Commentary: Some movement noticed early up. Bumrah goes for a length delivery outside off, moves away after taking the deck, Will has no issues in leaving this one alone.
On a good length on off, Pucovski blocks this one out.
Another length delivery outside off, Will shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off again, on a length, Will watchfully let this one through to Pant.
SWING AND A MISS! Bumrah, this time, drags his length back and bowls it on a shorter length on middle, Will looks to pull but misses. A tame appeal by Pant for caught behind but no says the umpire.
On off, well kept out. A steady start by Bumrah and also a maiden to start off.
Warner and Australia open their account in this game! On a length outside off, Warner punches this one through the cover-point region to pick up a brace.
Length again, this time, and on middle and leg, David clips this one to the fine leg region for a single.
Length and on off, Will is solid in his defense.
Down the leg side, Will looks to flick this one but he misses his shot.
Pucovski is up and running! His first runs in Test cricket. Length on middle and leg, Will flicks this one to the fine leg region to pick up a run.
Quick run. On off, Warner taps this to the off side and runs across for a quick single.
On off, blocked to the off side.
On a length and around off, David pushes this to the cover region and picks up a single.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, again, Will pushes this one back towards Jasprit.
Good length on off, WP pushes this to the off side to complete the over.
Length delivery on off, Warner defends it to point.
BEATEN! Back of a length outside off, Warner looks to swing at it but misses it.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! India draw first blood! Warner's comeback does not end on a happy note for the left-hander and for the Aussies! Siraj, again, continues his good form in this Test series and he breaks this new opening stand. Siraj dishes this on a length around off, it moves away after pitching, Warner is drawn into the shot and he swings his blade at this. He can only induce an outside edge and the ball flies towards the slip cordon. Pujara is the man there at first slip and he is not going to drop this.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs.
Length ball outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! Good length delivery outside off, Marnus looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski offers a solid defense on this one.
Length delivery on off, Will keeps it out.
Back of a length on middle, Pucovski flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside off, Marnus does not bother to play at that.
Length delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it towards the leg side.
Back of a length down the leg side, Pucovski looks to flick but misses it.
Good length ball on off, Pucovski defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! First boundary of the innings! Short of a length delivery on middle, Pucovski looks to pull but gets a top edge. It goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Pucovski drives it through mid on. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Outside off, Labuschagne lets it go.
Back of a length delivery and around off, WP hops and keeps it out well.
On middle, Will flicks it through the square leg region and picks up a couple.
On off, Pucovski pushes this towards point.
Short and around off, Will dabs this one away to the point region. Bumrah needs to try some more short balls when he is bowling to Pucovski.
A full ball on off, Will drives this one to the mid on region.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
A back of a length ball on middle, worked to the leg side.
On a good length around off, Will pushes this to the cover region.
An appeal for LBW but turned down. A back of a length ball around middle and leg, Will looks to tuck it away but misses to get hit high on the pads. An appeal but no says the umpire.
Confident push by Will. Gets three runs on this occasion. On a length and around off, Pucovski punches this one through the mid off region and will collect three runs.
Similar ball as the last delivery, this time it is Marnus, he punches this one through the mid off region and the fielder gives it chase and stops it before the ropes. The batters collect three runs.
Good length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Length delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket. The fielder there, dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Length ball outside off, Marnus offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on off, Marnus defends it to mid off.
Outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Length ball on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot.
On off, blocked out.
Another length ball on off, Pucovski fends this one out.
Siraj, this time, drags his length back and bowls a shorter one around off, Will sways away from the line of the ball.
Shorter and on the body, Pucovski fends this one to the short fine leg region.
Short again, down the leg side, WP just lets this one through to the keeper. A maiden by Siraj.
Short of a length this time, around off, it nips back in after pitching, Marnus does really well in leaving this one alone.
On off, ML looks to block but the ball takes the inside edge and hits the pads.
Outside off, shorter in length, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Another length delivery outside off, Marnus lets this one through in typical Marnus Labuschagne fashion. Swings his bat in the followthrough.

FOUR. Good shot. Marnus takes the ball on this time and he dispatches this one to the ropes. This one is shorter in length and on middle, Labuschagne swivel-pulls this one to the deep square leg region to find the ropes.
Quicker and shorter on middle, ML sits under this one.
On off, pushed to the short mid on fielder.
Length delivery around the off pole, WP pushes it back towards Siraj, who catches this one on his followthrough.

Very nice shot to collect three runs. Siraj bowls in a back of a length ball around off, Will hops and tucks this one through the mid-wicket region and Ashwin gives it a chase and pulls it back before the ropes. Saves one run for his side.
Good length on off, blocked out by Marnus. 'NO RUNNNNN', says Marnus, in regard to the single.
On off, kept out to the leg side.
On off, Labuschagne is solid in his defense.
Angled in from around off, kept out by Will. He denies the single on this occasion.
On a length and around the off pole, Pucovski punches this one with a straight blade to the mid on region.
Goes fuller and on middle this time, flicked away to the mid-wicket region for a single. Will moves to 21 from 45 balls with this single.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.

Quick single this time. Angles in a good length ball around off, Labuschagne taps this one to the off side and scampers for the single. Will responds and runs in. Bumrah runs in and has a shy at the striker's end but he misses.
Bouncer outside off, WP sways away and lets it go.
Flatter and on middle, ML keeps it out. 'Come on Ash, come on Ash', is the call from Pant, behind the stumps.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Floated on middle, flicked to the square leg region.
On off, blocked out.
Loopy and on middle, Marnus skips down the track and works it through mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted and on middle, pushed to the mid on region. Just the single off Ashwin's first over.
Slightly behind the good length area and around off, ML pushes this to the leg side.
Goes to bowl a good length delivery outside off this time, Labuschagne plays this to the cover region.

EDGED...SHORT! Ohhh..great bowling by Bumrah! He almost gets the big wicket of Marnus but the ball falls short of the fielder there. On a good length around off, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards Pujara, at first slip, but the ball falls short.
BEATEN. Lovely bowling by Jasprit. Again, he goes to bowl a good length just around off, ML looks to block this one out but the ball takes the outside edge and goes into Pant's mitts.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Well played by Marnus! He sends this one past the ropes! On a fuller length around off, Labuschagne punches this one through the mid on region, where the fielder dives, but is not able to stop the ball, which then runs past the ropes.
Flatter and on middle, clipped to the leg side.
Short and around off, spins back in, Will pushes this to the leg side off his back foot.
Short again and outside off, Pucovski punches this one through the cover region and picks up a brace.
Flatter and around off, WP defends this one out off his back foot, back towards Ashwin.
On off, worked to the off side.
On off again, Pucovski keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Length ball on off, Marnus offers a solid defense to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne pushes it towards mid on for a single.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Pucovski looks to push but misses it due to the extra bounce on this one.
Length ball on middle, Pucovski flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards the leg side.
Flighted ball on off, Labuschagne punches it to covers.
Floated delivery on middle, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
Just a gentle push, this. Full delivery on off, Labuschagne pushes it through covers for a couple.
On middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Labuschagne offers a solid defense on this one.
Good length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot towards point. Good communication by Will as he is quick to deny the single, whenever he feels there isn't one on offer.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot. Quick, early call again by Pucovski to say no to the single.
Length delivery on off, Will blocks it off the back foot.
Bouncer on middle, Pucovski does well to duck under it.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski punches it to covers. A good punch by Will but it was straight to the fielder.
Length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it out towards the mid on region. Maiden by Bumrah.

Tossed up delivery on off, Labuschagne skips down the track and works this to the cover region. Thinks about the single, comes a few paces down the deck, but then decides otherwise and sends Will back.
Flighted ball on off, Labuschagne offers a solid defense on this one.
BEATEN! Short and outside off, Marnus looks to cut but misses it.
On off, Labuschagne blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to short fine leg.
Floated delivery on off, Marnus keeps it out. A maiden over from Ashwin.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Full again on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery on middle, Marnus blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on middle, Labuschagne pulls it to sqaure leg, where Jadeja makes a good stop.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it to square leg.
Floated ball on off, Pucovski keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Will punches it to covers.
Flighted delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it towards the leg side.
Full on off, Pucovski drives it through covers for a couple.

DROPPED! Pant is the culprit here. He should have taken it and the debutant is handed another life. Tossed up on off, Pucovski looks to defend but gets a slight outside edge. It goes towards the keeper where Pant tries to take with one hand but spills it. Rishabh will be disappointed with this one.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Down the leg side, Labuschagne looks to flick but misses it.
Back of a length on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Full on middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Floated on middle, Will tucks it to the square leg region.

FOUR! Good footwork by Will and he bags a boundary! Also, brings up 50 runs for the Aussies. Short and outside off, Pucovski makes some room and slaps this one through the cover region, past the diving fielder there and into the ropes.
On off, blocked.
Two, this time. Flatter again and outside off, Will rocks on his back foot and punches this one through the point region to pick up a couple of runs.
On off, WP pushes it back to the bowler.
Floats it nicely around off, Pucovski blocks this one out as well. Six runs off this over.
Length delivery around the off pole, Marnus looks to block this one out but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes through the point region. One run.
On off, kept out solidly. Pucovski is at 32 runs off 76 balls. A good, solid start to his Test career so far for the debutant.
Bumper on middle, WP knows what he has to do. Sits under this one.
Angles in a good length delivery on off, Will punches this to the cover region.
On off, tapped to cover-point. Pucovski first thinks about exchanging ends but then raises his blade and lets Marnus know that the single is not possible now.

NOT OUT! Pucovski survives! It looks like Pant did not take a clean catch, after all. The third umpire thinks he has enough evidence to suggest that Rishabh did not take a clean catch. Siraj bangs in a short ball on middle, Pucovski goes for the pull shot but he is only able to glove this one and the ball lobs over Pant. He turns around, runs a little and then takes it, but the ball pops out. He has a second attempt at this and seems to have taken it. The umpire's take this upstairs and want to have a look at this, which is then deemed to have dropped on the ground before he caught it on the second attempt. Will be not out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards the leg side.
Flighted ball on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
On middle, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it towards fine leg for a run.
On middle, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated delivery on middle, Labuschagne sweeps it to square leg.
Good length delivery on off, Pucovski looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. A tame appeal by the players but no says the umpire. Looked to be way too high.
Back of a length on off, Will defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Pucovski flicks it through square leg for a single.
Length delivery outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Length ball on off, Marnus defends it out.
On off, blocked out.
Flatter and on middle, tucked to the leg side. No run is the call by Will.
Short and around off, WP punches this one to the cover region and rotates the strike.

FOUR! Marnus sends one to the ropes now! Uses the crease well on this occasion. Ashwin, again goes for a short delivery around off, Labuschagne goes back deep in his crease and slaps this one through the cover region again and the ball speeds away to the ropes.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Labuschagne! The man in the deep tried to stop this one but he failed! Flatter on middle, Marnus flicks this one through the square leg region and the ball touches the ropes, as the fielder tried to stop it.
On off, blocked out.
Short and around off, Pucovski judges this well, gets on top of the bounce and hooks this one through the mid-wicket region. Picks up a couple. Moves to 37 now, does Pucovski.
On a length and around off, Will pushes this one to the cover region, where he finds the man.
On off, blocked to the off side. No is the call for the single. A loud, clear no as well.
Angles in a good length ball around off, Will punches this to the point region.

Big mix-up between the batters but luckily, this does not result in a tragedy for the Aussies. On a shorter length around off, Pucovski punches this one through the cover region. The batters complete two runs. Will is interested in the third but Marnus says no, but Pucovski is halfway down the track. Bumrah, though, slips in the process of sending the throw and can only send it to the man at the edge of the cover-point region. By the time, the man there can fire in a throw to Pant, Pucovski makes it in. Scary sign for the hosts.
Siraj continues to pepper Pucovski with a short ball around off, Pucovski pulls this one nicely though through mid-wicket and he picks up three runs.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Pucovski pushes it to mid on.
Flighted ball on off, Pucovski punches it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it just before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Loopy delivery on off, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
On middle, Labuschagne flicks it to short leg.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Short delivery on off, Labuschagne punches it through covers for a boundary.
On middle, Labuschagne plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg. The batsmen get two runs.

FOUR! Cracking shot! What a welcome this is to International Test cricket for Saini! This is from a debutant to a debutant and Will sends this one to the ropes. Short delivery on off, Pucovski punches it through covers for a boundary. He also moves onto 49 with this shot.

FOUR! 50 for Will Pucovski! It has been a fine innings from him on debut! Sure, he has got a couple of lives here but he has still shown his class with his strokeplay and he will be hoping to turn this into a big, big score. Short delivery on middle, Pucovski pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Will leaves it alone.
Length delivery on off, Will punches it through point for a single.
Back of a length outside off, Labuschagne lets it go. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
On off, well kept out.
On a good length around off, Will pushes this to the cover region for a single.
Back of a length ball around off, Labuschagne blocks this one out.
Another length delivery around off, ML pushes this to the cover region.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off again, left alone again.
Length delivery outside off, Pucovski punches it through covers for a couple.
Back of a length on off, Pucovski pushes it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Pucovski defends it off the back foot.
Full on middle, Pucovski pushes it through mid on. Jadeja chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Back of a length on off, Marnus keeps it out.
Length ball on off, Labuschagne pushes it towards point for a single. 100 up for Australia.
Short of a length delivery around the off pole, well blocked out by Labuschagne.
On off, pushed towards the mid on region.
A comfortable three this time. On a length around off, ML pushes this one nicely through the mid on region and Ashwin gives it chase. Does well to stop it before the ropes. Collects three runs.
On middle, knocked towards the mid on region.
Bouncer on middle, Pucovski ducks under this one.

Gets away with this one as there was no fielder in the deep. On a shortish length around off, Will hooks this one to the deep square leg region aerially. The ball, though, lands safe as there was no fielder there. The batters collect two runs.

100 partnership up between these two. Wonderful batting by them so far and they will look to continue. On a good length on middle, Marnus flicks this one to the mid-wicket region and a misfield will mean that they can collect a single.

OUT! LBW! Saini has his first wicket! What a moment this is for the youngster! A debutant gets the other debutant and Saini is ecstatic. India needed to break this partnership and Navdeep has decided to take matters into his own hands. He bowls this on a length outside off, moves in after taking the deck, Pucovski takes too long to get his bat across and misses his flick away. Gets rapped on the pads. The players appeal and the umpire obliges raising his finger. Will is not going to review this one as he knows that this was plumb. A fine, fine stand comes to an end.
NO BALL. On a good length around off, Smith pushes this back to the bowler. Also, a No Ball as Saini had overstepped.
A full ball on middle, Smith clips this to the leg side and opens his account for this game.
On off, blocked.
Another full delivery around off, Marnus drives this towards the mid on region but the fielder there does well to dive and stop this one. They do not go for the run as well.
On off, Labuschagne is solid in his defense. A very good over from Saini comes to an end. Just 2 runs and a wicket of this over.
On off, well kept out.
Length and on off, Steven blocks it out. 'No run', is his call to Marnus.
On off, worked to the leg side. Smith strides forward, thinking about the single but then sends Labuschagne back as well.
On off, pushed to the mid on region.
Bumper on middle, SS ducks under this one.

FOUR! SWEET SHOT! Smith is looking aggressive in his approach and he punches this one away to the ropes. Bumrah goes for a length delivery around off, Smith, uses the pace on the ball and then hammers this one through the mid off region to bag a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Goes fuller and on middle this time, Labuschagne tickles this one to the fine leg region to run across for a single.
FOUR! SHOT! Goes down the ground again, fetches the boundary ropes again! Smith is looking in fine touch! A length delivery, around off, Smith punches this one through mid on and finds the ropes.
On off, kept out by Steven.
FOUR! Another one! Great timing on this one. On a good length, straying on the pads, Smith clips this one through the square leg region for another boundary.
On middle, SS plays this one to the mid-wicket region. 9 runs off this over.
Good length delivery around the off pole, Marnus dabs this one through point for a quick single.
On middle, knocked to the mid-wicket region for one.
Length delivery around off, Labuschagne plays this with a straight bat to the fielder at mid on.
On off, worked to the leg side.
Angles in a good length ball on off, Marnus is solid in his defense.
On middle, clipped straight to the man at short mid-wicket. A good, tight over by Boom Boom comes to a close. Just 2 runs conceded.
Down the leg side, SS misses this tuck away. This goes just around the leg pole.
On a length on off, Smith tucks this to deep mid-wicket to rotate the strike.
On off, blocked out.
On off, tapped to the off side.
Short of a length on middle, worked to the leg gully fielder.
Behind the good length slightly and on middle, Marnus works this through square leg and will retain the strike for the next over with a single.
On off, pushed this with soft hands through the cover region for a single.
Flatter and on middle, Steven plays this with a straight bat to the mid on region.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and on middle, tucked away to the fielder at short leg.
On off, worked to the leg side.

FOUR! Smith is definitely ready for this game! He is playing some good strokes! Floats it up nicely, does Ashwin, and dishes this one on middle, Smith clips this one through mid-wicket for a boundary. Smith moves to 19 off just 20 balls. He does not want to let Ashwin get into his rhythm.
Back of a length on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball on off, Smith blocks it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Smith offers a solid defense on this one.
Back of a length on middle, Smith flicks it to square leg.
Length delivery on middle, Smith flicks it through square leg for a single.

FOUR! Nice use of the feet! Tossed up delivery on middle, Smith comes down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary. Some more aggression being shown by Smith. Wants to dominate Ashwin now, does he! Also, moves to 24 off 25 deliveries.
Floated ball on middle, Smith flicks it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery on middle, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket.
On off, Smith keeps it out.
Floated delivery on middle, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket.
A tame appeal for caught behind but turned down. Flatter and around middle and leg, Smith looks to flick but misses. A very light appeal but no says the umpire. Smith agrees as well, as he nods.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

FOUR! 50 for Marnus Labuschagne! Full delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it through covers for a boundary. His ninth in Test cricket and his first one against India. He has looked real good out there and will want to convert this double digit score into a three digit score.
Good length ball on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot! Full ball on off, Marnus drives it through mid off for a boundary. Taking the charge now, is Marnus. Boundaries are coming in good quantity for the Aussies.
Full on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards fine leg for a couple. 12 runs have come from this over.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Smith pushes it through mid on for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through square leg for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Smith comes down the track and pushes it through mid on for a run. 150 up for Australia as well.
On middle, Labuschagne sweeps it to short fine leg.
Floated delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up ball on middle, Labuschagne pushes it through mid on for a single.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it to mid off.

BEATEN! That is a beauty of a delivery! Good length delivery just outside off, comes back in sharply after taking the deck, Labuschagne looks to defend but misses it and the ball whizzes past the inside edge into Pant's mitts.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it back towards the bowler.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Marnus offers a solid defense on this one. A maiden, this time around, for Siraj.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on off, Smith looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
On middle, Smith flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up ball on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne defends it back towards the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Good piece of fielding, Rohit Sharma. On middle, ML clips this one through the mid-wicket region where Rohit gets low and stops this one.
On middle, clipped to the leg side and the batters cross ends.
On off, well defended.
On off, well kept out again by Smith to see off this over.
Flatter and on middle, worked to the leg side by Marnus.
Flighted and on middle, Labuschagne tucks this to the short leg fielder.

FOUR! Fifty partnership up between these two as well. Good batting by them so far. Floated on off, Labuschagne skips down the track and lofts this one over the bowler's head and it crosses the ropes on a couple of bounces.
On middle, pushed to the leg side.
On middle, blocked out.
Floated and around off, ML keeps it out.
Floated around off, Smith pushes this to the covers.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and on middle, tucked to the short leg fielder.
On off, kept out by Steven.
Short and wide outside off, Smith shoulders arms to this one. He would have been tempted to slash his blade at this but he does not fall for his temptation.
On off, blocked out. A good start by Jadeja, a maiden to begin his bowling spell.
Flatter and around middle and leg, tucked to the leg side for a single.

A catch has been taken but the umpire says not out. Rahane kept waiting, thinking about taking the review, but does not do so in the end. Floated on middle and leg, Smith looks to tuck it away but misses and the ball comes off the pads and lobs near short leg. The catch is taken there and an appeal follows. No says the umpire. There is some discussion going around but in the end, Rahane is not convinced enough, to go for the review.
On off, worked through mid on for a single.
On off again, blocked out.
Flighted and around off, Marnus tucks this to the mid-wicket region.
Floated and on off, Marnus tucks this to mid-wicket again but he finds Rohit Sharma, who fakes a throw at the non-striker's end and then smiles when Smith has a look his way.
Tossed up delivery on off, Smith pushes it back towards the bowler.
Flighted ball on middle, Smith defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Smith keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, Smith pushes it towards the off side.
On off, Smith keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Smith blocks it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Labuschagne defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne comes down the track and drives it back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery on leg, Marnus looks to sweep but gets hit on the pads.
On middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up ball on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle and leg, Smith pads it away.
Flighted ball on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Smith flicks it towards the leg side.
On off, Smith keeps it out.
Floated ball on middle, Smith defends it off the back foot.
On middle, Smith flicks it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Smith keeps it out.
Down the leg side, Smith lets it go.
Floated delivery on middle, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, Smith pushes it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up ball on middle, Smith flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Down the leg side, Labuschagne flicks it to short leg.
Bouncer on leg, Smith does well to duck under it.
Bumper again on leg, Smith sits under it.
Back of a length on off, Smith pushes it towards point for a single.
Length delivery on leg, Labuschagne flicks it to square leg.
Back of a length on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Length ball on leg, Marnus flicks it towards the leg side. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Siraj starts off with a back of a length delivery on middle, Smith works this to the square leg region.
Slips this one down the leg side, does Siraj. No stroke offered to this delivery by Smith.
Slight behind the good length and around middle, Steven tucks this to the leg side but finds the man at square leg again. Tells Marnus to wait on the single.
SWING AND A MISS. Siraj, this time, bangs this in short and on middle, Smith looks to pull this one but does not connect bat with ball. Worth a try on this pitch.
Short, again and on the body, Smith works this to the leg side and crosses over for the single. The first runs on Day 2.
On middle, pushed to the short mid-wicket fielder.

FOUR. Brilliantly played by Smith. First boundary of the Day. Easy pickings for Smith. A half-volley around the off pole, Smith leans in and drives the ball through the cover region and he bags a boundary.
On off, tapped to the off side for a quick single. Good running by these two.
On middle, tucked to the mid-wicket region. Marnus, is quick, to deny the single on this occasion.
On a good length on middle, Marnus works this to the mid-wicket region again.

BEATEN. Excellent delivery from Bumrah. He bowls in a good length delivery outside off, Marnus looks to block this one out but the ball nips away, misses the outside edge and goes into Rishabh's mitts.
On middle, flicked to the leg side. 5 runs off Bumrah's first over.
Slightly behind the good length and on middle, Smith fends this off to square leg. 'WAIT, WAIT, WAITTT', says Smith, to Labuschagne, in regard to the single.
On off, tapped to the cover region.
On middle again, tucked to square leg. Smith, again is clear in denying the single. Marnus replies with a melodic 'NO RUNNNNN'. Quite quirky to have these two out together.
On off, blocked out.
Short and around off, Steven pulls this one to the mid-wicket region to pick up a couple of runs.
On middle, Smith gets across and pushes this one to the mid-wicket region to retain the strike for the next over, with a single.
On off, SS taps it to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Little bit more bounce here. Bumrah dishes a back of a length delivery around off, Smith gets his bat up and the bounce gets slightly big on him. He still manages to keep it out.
On middle and leg, Smith looks to tuck it away but misses and ball goes to the leg side off his thigh pad. A tame appeal from Bumrah, but nothing doing says the umpire.
On off, kept out.
Back of a length and around off, Steven nudges this to square leg.
Length and around off, worked to square leg again. A maiden over by India's premium bowler, Bumrah.
On a good length around off, ML solidly pushes this to the mid on region.
On off, worked to the leg side.
Angles in a length delivery around off, Labuschagne is solid in his defense.

Three this time. Nicely placed by Marnus. Finds a gap in between the fielder. Fuller and on middle, Marnus flicks this one through the mid-wicket region and the ball runs away. Ashwin gives it a chase and stops it before the ropes. Saves a run for his side.
On middle, worked to the leg side again.
On a length and on middle, Smith tucks it to the fielder at square leg.
Length ball around off, pushed straight to the cover fielder.
Length ball around off, Marnus tucks this one to the leg side.
Similar ball angling into Marnus, he tucks this one towards square leg for no run.
On middle, Marnus plays it straight to short mid-wicket.
Slightly shortish around leg, Marnus tucks this one towards the fine leg area for a single.
Length ball around middle, Smith blocks it solidly.
Length ball around off, Marnus defends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly fuller around off, pushed towards covers.
Good fielding. Shortish outside off, Marnus cuts it towards the gully region. Rahane there dives to his right and saves a certain boundary.
Length around off, Marnus pushes it towards mid off.
Length ball on middle, Marnus plays that with a straight bat back to the bowler.
Length ball around off comes back in a little, Marnus plays that with soft hands towards cover and takes a quick run. Good testing over this by Siraj.
On off, tucked to the leg side.
Floated on off, ML is solid in his defense.
Shortish around off, Labuschagne whips this one to the square leg region and exchanges ends with Smith.
Flighted on off, Smith prods forward and blocks this one out.
On off, SS works this towards mid on for a good, quick single.
Flighted outside off, Marnus drives this nicely but finds the fielder at covers.
On off, pushed to the leg side.

NOT OUT! A good call by the umpire and the on-field decision stays on. Siraj bowls in a back of a length delivery around middle, Smith looks to fend this one away to the leg side but misses and gets rapped on the pads. An appeal but no says the umpire. Rahane looks around, has a quick chat and makes the 'T' symbol. Hot Spot rolls in and there is not bat on this. Ball Tracker rolls in and two reds and wickets....MISSING. The height was an issue. India lose a review and Smith does not have to walk back.
On middle, flicked to the mid-wicket region for a quick run.
Good length and on off, tucked to square leg.
On off, ML keeps it out.
Short of a length and around off, ML tucks this to the leg side.
On off, blocked out.
Floated on off, SS pushes this to covers.
Floated on off, Steven skips down the track and pushes this back towards Jadeja.
On off, played to the fielder at covers.
Short and around off, Steven goes on his back foot and blocks.
On middle, Smudge, again is solid in his defensive push. Maiden over for Jadeja.
Fuller length on middle, Marnus plays it with a straight bat towards silly mid on.
FOUR! Aerial but safe. A length ball around middle, Labuschagne flicks this one past the diving fielder at square leg and collects his first boundary for the morning.
Length ball around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Length around off, Labuschagne rocks back and flicks this one through the gap at mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball around off, Smith dead bats it with a straight bat, back towards the bowler.
Length ball on off, Smith blocks this out.
FOUR! What a good shot! Slashes this one wonderfully. Flat and around off, Labuschagne makes some room and slashes this one through the point region and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
Down the leg side, left alone.
On middle, pushed to the mid on region.
Loopy on off, ML drives this one to the cover region but finds Ashwin there.
On off, worked to the leg side.
Looks to find the gap again but finds the man on this occasion. Flat and outside off, ML camps back and cuts this one but only finds the point fielder there.
Flat and on middle, tucked to short leg.
Smith giving the charge now to Ashwin. Looking to be positive here, is Smith. Floated and on off, Steven skips down the track and works this to the leg side.
On middle, tucked to square leg.
Flatter and around off, Ashwin punches this one to the cover region for a single.
Flighted on middle, ML skips down the track and chips this one over the mid-wicket region for another single.
Flatter again and around off, SS rocks on his back foot and punches this one through the cover region to pick up another single.
On off, blocked out.
Flat and on off, Smith clips this one through square leg for one.

Three, this time. Short and around off, ML cuts this one through the point region and the man there gives chase. Stops it before the ropes. They pushed for the third and got it without any hitches, in the end.
On off, pushed to covers.
Flatter and on middle and leg, Smith goes back and works this one through the square leg region and picks up two runs. 200 runs up for Australia as well.
On off, pushed back to Jadeja.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Short and around off, punched to covers.
Flatter and on middle, ML gives the charge and clips this to the mid-wicket region. One run.
Short and on middle and leg, SS fends this one out.
Loopy on middle, Steven blocks this one off his front foot.
On middle, tucked to the square leg region this time.
Short and wide, punched towards the fielder at cover.
Fuller this time around leg, Marnus flicks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! This time Labuschagne doesn't miss out. A short and wide ball, he rocks back and cuts it through cover point to collect a boundary. Also 100-run partnership comes up between Smith and Labuschagne with that shot. Marnus moves into the 90's now.
Flatter around off, fended on the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jadeja gets the breakthrough and Marnus, who was looking to get to his ton loses his wicket. The skipper takes a really good catch. Makes it to 91, but will not be able to cross the triple digit mark. Just the wicket that India needed and also at the right time. Jadeja goes for a short one and around the off pole, Labuschagne camps on his back foot and looks to punch this one away but the ball bounces a tad bit more and also spins away slightly, just enough to take the outside edge and go towards the first slip region, where Rahane gets low and makes no mistake. A sad end to Marnus' innings.
Wade is off the mark straightaway with a sweep. A fullish ball around off, Wade goes down and sweeps this one fine towards fine leg for a brace. A successful over this by Jadeja.
On middle, tucked to square leg.
Floated on off, Smith punches this one to the fielder at mid on.
On middle, flicked to the leg side again.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR STEVEN SMITH! His 30th Test half-century and his fourth against India and he will be very happy with this. Will be looking to cross that magical 100 number now. Has struggled in this series but this innings has been very brave from him. Floated and on off, Smith punches this one down the ground and beats the fielder there to find the ropes.
On off, blocked.
On off, bunted down towards long on for one.
On off, punched to mid off.
On middle, blocked out.
Short and around off, SS skips down the track and just taps it to the off side.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated around off, Steven punches this but finds the cover fielder.
FOUR! Well played! Floated on off, Smith drives this one through the cover region and finds the fence. Smith continues on his merry way.
Flighted and outside off, Wade plays this with soft hands, towards the point region.
On off, MW keeps this one out well.
Flighted again and around off, Wade pushes this to the cover region. Also quick to deny the single.
On middle, Wade turns this to the mid-wicket region and rotates the strike.
Down the leg side, SS looks to play at this but is not able to connect bat with ball.
On middle, Steven works this to the fielder at short mid on. Just the solitary run off this over.
Floated on off, Wade sweeps this one but finds the man there at short leg, Vihari, who gets hit on his calf. Ouch. Would have stung, that.

FOUR! SMACKED! Wade is good at playing these shots and he shows it again. Tosses it up and lands it around off, Wade punches this one through the extra cover region and the ball speeds away to the ropes.

OUCH, VIHARI. He gets hit again. What bad luck this is for him. Wade again, who looks to sweep but ends up hitting Vihari on the body. He is down but he gets back up quickly, should be okay to continue again.
On off, swept to square leg. Misses Vihari this time though, luckily.
On off, well kept out.
Loopy on off, Wade blocks it out again.
Shortsh around off, pushed towards mid off.
Fuller around off, Smith pushes it to mid off.

FOUR! Nicely done. Floated on middle and leg, Smith goes for the sweep and connects that well. The ball races away through the gap at square leg area for a boundary. Smith showing some aggression against Ashwin here.
Flatter around off, pushed to silly mid on.
Flatter around off, Smith tucks it towards square leg.
On off, Smith is solid in his defense as he blocks this out.
FOUR! Good shot by Wade again! Gets another boundary. Floated on off, Wade punches this one through the mid on region to bag another boundary.
Gets Vihari again, does Wade. On off, swept by Wade towards Vihari, who sways away but he does get hit. Vihari will be waiting for the new ball, more than anybody else out there.
On off, punched to the deep cover region for a brace.
Flighted and on off, Wade blocks it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jadeja gets another wicket and sends another batter to the hut! There is always a sense of adventure about Wade and that adventure has made sure that he loses his wicket. He was looking good with his short stay out in the middle but that has been cut short by Jadeja and he is doing well to get wickets at regular intervals. Wade skips down the track as Jadeja goes for a flatter delivery around middle, Wade looks to tuck this one away to the leg side but he gets a leading edge and the ball balloons towards the mid on region, where Bumrah takes a good catch.
On off, Green blocks this one out nicely.
Tossed up outside off, Smith drives this one through covers for a brace as Jadeja there chases it down and keeps it to two.
On middle, Smith pushes it down towards long on for a run.
Flatter around off, blocked towards first slip.
Floated around middle and off, Green looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. A bit of appeal by Ashwin and Pant but the umpire is unmoved.
On middle, played towards silly mid on.
Floated on middle, Green blocks this out.
On off, blocked out.
FOUR! Smith is marching on at the moment, regardless of who partners him at the other end. Flatter and outside off, Smith cuts this one through the point region to bag a boundary.
On off, pushed to mid on.
FOUR! He is so good at reading the length and he dispatches this one too! Short and around off, Smith punches this one through covers for a boundary.
On off, pushed to covers for one.
On off, driven to mid off.
Floated on off, kept out.
On off, tucked to square leg this time.
Short and around leg, SS tucks this one towards fine leg for an easy single.
On off, well kept out.
Flat and on middle, nudged to short leg.
On middle, pushed to the off side.
On a good length outside off, Smith lets this one through to Pant.
Outside off again, some away movement noticed, Steven has no issues in letting this one through.
Outside off again, Smith leaves it again. Bumrah is looking to bowl in that fourth and fifth stump channel now.
Similar delivery as the last ball, same shot offered by Smith, which is basically no shot. Left alone.
Now decides to put bat to ball. Length and around off, SS pushes this to the cover region.
BEATEN. Ohhh...ripper. What a delivery. A back of a length delivery around off, nips away after taking the deck, Smith looks to defend but gets beaten all ends up. A good, testing over by Bumrah.
WIDE. Way too wide outside off, Green leaves it alone. Wided.
Outside off again, inside the tramline this time though, Green, again offers no shot to this.
A full ball around off, Green digs this one out to the cover-point region.
Good shot but for no runs this time. A fuller length delivery around off, Green drives this one very nicely towards mid on and Ashwin does well to run to his left, dive and stop this one.
Outside off, left alone.
Full on off, nips back in slightly, Cameron drives this to the fielder at mid off.
Outside off again, CG does not want to have a poke at this.
Slightly behind the good length and on the stumps, Smith blocks this one out solidly.
Outside off, Smith lets this one through to the keeper.
Angles in a delivery around off, Smith blocks this one out as well. A good, solid block offered by Steven. A good battle this, between Smith and Bumrah.
On a length outside off, Smith raises his blade and lets this one go. Smith is resisting his temptations to have a poke at the deliveries that are outside off.
Short and around off, pulled towards the mid-wicket region for one.
Good leave by Green to see off Bumrah's over. Outside off, CG raises his bat and leaves this one nicely.
Fullish around off, Smith drives it straight to mid on.
Length around off, Smith defends it back to the bowler.
On a length in the channel outside off, Smith lets it go.
Similar ball outside off, Smith is not interested in playing at that.
Slightly fuller outside off, Smith shoulders arms to that.
Length around middle, Smith tucks it towards the left of fine leg and comes back for a couple of runs.
Length ball around off, Green blocks this out on the off side.
BEATEN! A fuller length delivery, inviting the drive, outside off, Green looks to drive but misses the ball and gets beaten altogether.
Shortish outside off, this time Green lets it go.
A bumper on middle now, Green does well to duck under that.

OUT! LBW! Excellent bowling this by Bumrah. Green goes for a duck. After dishing out balls outside off, Bumrah bowls a length ball around off, makes it to jag back in. Green looks to defend but gets beaten by the pace and movement to get hit on the pads. The Indians appeal and the umpire obliges by raising his finger. Green has a word with Smith but decides against the review. A good decision as replays show that this would go onto hit the stumps. Green does not hang around for long.
On a good length outside off, Paine lets this one through.
A back of a length delivery outside off, punched to the cover region.
On off, SS looks to drive but the ball takes the inside edge and hits his pads.
On off, pushed to the off side.
A back of a length delivery around off, Steven blocks this one out.
On off, well kept out.
Angles in a delivery around off, Smith taps this towards point and signals no for the single, on this occasion.
Short of a length and around off, the skipper pushes this to the mid on region.
Outside off on a good length, Paine shoulders arms to this one.
On off again this time, Tim plays a solid defensive push back towards Boom Boom.
Length and outside off, TP just lets this one through to Pant.
On off, good length, driven but straight to the fielder at short cover. A good start this has been by Bumrah.
On off, blocked out by Tim.
Outside off, keeps slightly low as well, Smith lets it go.
Good length on off and middle, Steven defends this one out with a straight bat.
Angled into off and middle, Smith helps this one through the backward square leg region for a brace. Also, brings up the 250 runs mark for the Australians.
Short ball on middle, SS ducks under this one.
Slightly behind the good length and on the pads, Smith helps this one through mid-wicket for a single.

An appeal for LBW but turned down. Another back of a length ball around off, nips back in, Paine looks to leave this one but the ball goes onto hit him on his pads. Siraj appeals but nothing from the umpire. Height would have been an issue there. India do not opt for the review as well.
Length ball sliding down leg, tucked towards fine leg for a single.
Around off, Paine is off the mark with a push to the covers.
Length ball around off, Smith stands tall and defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length on off, Smith plays it in the gap at mid-wicket to change ends.

OUT! BOWLED! Knocked him over. Bumrah, you beauty! A fuller ball around off, comes back in slightly and Paine looks to have a push at this but plays it at the wrong line, there was not foot movement as well. The ball goes through the forward push of the Australian captain and goes onto disturb the timber behind. Bumrah has been lethal with the second new ball and has shown it again. Paine completely misjudged the line there and has to make his way back to the pavilion. Australia 6 down now.
Back of a length and down the leg side, Cummins lets this one go.

A stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire says no. A back of a length delivery around off, Smith looks to block this one out but the ball nips back in slightly and hits him high on the thigh pad. An appeal but no says the umpire. A discussion between Siraj and Rahane but in the end, they do not go for the review.
On off, pushed to mid on.
Short and on off, SS pulls this one to the backward square leg region for a single.
Short of a length and around off, PC keeps it out.
On off, blocked out.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
On a length around off, Smith shuffles and blocks this down towards mid on.
FOUR! A mere push. A short of a length around off, Smith stands tall and pushes this one through the covers for a boundary.
A fuller ball around middle, Smith shuffles and clips this one towards deep mid-wicket for a brace. Excellent batting here by Smith.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Back of a length on off, Smith tucks this one through mid-wicket for a single.
In the channel outside off, Cummins lets it go through to the keeper.
Back of a length outside off, Smith punches this one to the cover region.
FOUR! Brilliant. Absolutely brilliant. What a shot to get into your 90s. A fuller ball around off, Smith whips this one through the mid-wicket region, through the carpet, into the ropes.
Outside off, cut to deep point for a single.
On a length outside off, Cummins lets this one through to the keeper.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
Length and around off, moves back in after pitching, Cummins pushes this one to the cover region to see off Saini's first over for the Day.
Good length and around the off pole, Smith shuffles across and blocks this one out well.
On off, SS keeps it out.
On off, Smith pushes this to the leg side for a quick run. Moves onto 95 now.
Outside off, left alone by Patty.
FOUR BYES. Bonus runs for Australia. Bumrah dishes a bouncer on middle and leg, Cummins sits under this one. Pant hops to his left but is not able to stop this one. The ball runs away to the ropes.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Steven looks to have a push at this but the ball takes the inner half of the willow and hits his pads and rolls to the leg side.
Moves to 97 now. A back of a length delivery outside off, Smith slaps this one through the point region and picks up two runs before the fielder in the deep can run across to his left and stop this.
Good length and around off, SS is solid in keeping this one out.
Another length delivery around off, Smudge pushes this to the cover region.
On off, well kept out again.
Three runs off the over. Shortish and around off, Smith hooks this one to the deep mid-wicket region to retain the strike for the next over. Also, he is now just two runs away from his century.
Floated on off, blocked out.
On middle, pushed back to Ravindra.
Short and around off, Smudge punches this one through the cover region, off his back foot, for one. Moves to 99 now.
NO BALL. On off, pushed to the off side. Will also be a No Ball as Jadeja had overstepped.

OUT! TIMBER! Jadeja gets another one and the decision to bring on Jadeja is a masterclass by Rahane. Cummins goes back for a duck as well. Jadeja bowls this very full and around off, Cummins is late in getting his blade down in time to dig this one out. Cummins misses out. But the ball does not as it goes onto hit the off pole. A very good wicket for India and Australia lose their seventh wicket.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Floated on off, Starc pushes this to the cover region for a single.
PLAY AND A MISS. Good delivery by Saini. He bowls it full and around off, nips away, Starc looks for the drive but he misses his stroke and the ball goes towards Pant.
Short and on middle, took Starc by surprise as he got done by the extra bounce. He looked to block this one out but the ball took the glove and fell out onto the turf.
Play and a miss! On a length outside off, Starc misses his drive again. This is good bowling by Saini. Making Starc search for the runs, instead of handing it to him.
Short and down the leg side, MS lets it go.
On off, tapped to the cover region for a quick single. A misfield by Jadeja and the batters think about the second but Starc says no, in the end.
Length and on middle, tucked to the square leg region where Jadeja runs in and fields well. A loud 'no' by Smith to his partner. Will be on 99.
Floated on off, MS keeps it out off the front foot.
This time blocks it off the back foot towards mid on.
Another block towards the mid on region.
Short and on off, pushed back to the bowler.

EDGY! Three this time as well. Floated outside off, Starc lunges forward and looks to block this one out but the ball takes the outside edge and goes past the slip fielder and the batters take three runs.
On off, blocked back to Jaddu. Still on 99, is Smith. Nervy.
On off, kept out towards the off side.
FOUR! SHOT! Growing in confidence, is Starc. On a length on off, Mitchell lofts this one over the mid on region and he finds the ropes.
On off, tapped to cover-point and Starc yells a quick 'YEAH' to Smith and they cross ends. Smith is back on strike now. Is on 99 too.
Length and on off, SS pushes this to the off side. A quick 'no' to Starc. Still on 99.
Another length delivery on off, Smith pushes this to the mid-wicket region but it is Jadeja who is prowling that area and it is hard to sneak a run when you play the ball towards him.

There it is! HUNDRED FOR STEVEN SMITH! He has worked very hard for this and after his poor show in the first Two tests, he has bounced back well. A length delivery on off and middle, Smith shuffles across and tucks this one to the fine leg region and he collects three runs by the time the fielder can mop up in the deep. He has shown everyone what he can do and especially to those who were doubting him after the first two Tests. His 27th century in Tests and his 8th against India. Take a bow, champ!
Floated on middle, Smith plays it back to Jadeja.
Flatter around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up outside off, Smith lets it go.
Shorter around off, Smith cuts it well but straight to backward point.
NO BALL. Fullish ball on middle, Smith dances down the track and digs it out towards the bowler. But Jadeja has overstepped here.
On middle, fllicked straight to mid-wicket.
Fullish around off, driven straight to covers.
Bumper down the leg side, Starc lets this one go.
Another bouncer on off, MS sits under this one.
Short and around off, Starc looks to pull but the ball lobs off the splice of the blade and lands next to the turf, on the off side.
Short and on the body, Starc pulls this one to the deep square leg region for a single.
Length and on off, Smith dabs this one towards cover-point and the batters scamper through for the single.
NO BALL AND FOUR. Starc takes on Saini and dispatches him nicely. Short and on middle, Starc pulls this one to the fine leg region for a boundary. A No Ball too as Saini had overstepped.
Bouncer on off, Starc looks to hook it away but misses.
On off, driven to deep covers for a single. 300 up for Australia as well.
Floated on off, MS pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy and on off, MS pushes this one to the mid off region.
On off, Starc slogs this one to the deep square leg region for a single.
Loopy and around off, SS skips down the track and pads the ball away.
On off, pushed back to the bowler. A good over by Jadeja comes to an end.
Short ball on leg, Starc ducks and lets it go through to Pant.
NO BALL. That seems to have slipped out of Saini's hands. A beamer kind of ball outside off, Starc lets it go. Pant too fumbles while collecting it.
Shortish around middle, Starc looks to pull, but the ball misses his bat and goes through.

SIX! Clean strike. A shortish ball on middle, Starc sits back and pulls it all the way towards the deep mid-wicket boundary for a maximum. He then gives a glaring look at Saini who just turns around and walks back.
Short again and Starc goes for it again. This time he doesn't time it well enough and the ball just lands ahead of the fielder at mid on. Two taken by the batters.

OUT! CAUGHT! The rush of blood to Starc has made him lose his wicket! Shortish ball around middle and leg, Starc goes for the slog, but has no timing on that whatsoever. The ball balloons up in the air towards mid-wicket area, Gill from mid on runs to his left and completes an easy catch. A good cameo from Starc comes to an end. Australia 8 down now. How many more can they add now?

A length ball shapes away after pitching and goes through Lyon's outside edge. There was a noise as the ball passed the bat, but it seems the noise was from the pad. A bit of appeal by the bowler, but the umpire neglects it. No review either from Rahane.
FOUR! WHACKED! Floated on off, Smith gets on his knees and slog sweeps this one towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Outside off, punched to deep covers for one run.
On off, blocked.

OUT! LBW! That had to be plumb! Jadeja gets his fourth wicket of the game and even the review is not able to save Lyon. A full toss on off and middle, Lyon looks to play at this but he misses. It hits him on his boot. The players appeal and the umpire obliges, raising his finger. Lyon walks back but takes the review just to be sure. Ultra Edge shows not bat involved. Ball Tracker comes in and confirms that the on-field call is the right one. One last wicket remaining to take for the Indians.
On off, JH pushes this to the off side.
On off, blocked.
Shortish outside off, Smith gives himself room and slaps this one aerially in the gap at covers and comes back for a second. He will look to keep strike this over.
FOUR! Nicely done. A shortish ball outside off, Smith waits for it and upper cuts this one above the slips to get himself another boundary.
Fuller on off this time from Bumrah, Smith makes room and drives this one towards cover and takes a single. Hazlewood to face Bumrah now.
On a length around off, Hazlewood pushes it with soft hands towards covers and takes a quick run. This is not good from India, giving Hazlewood a single.
Three more taken. A fullish ball on middle, Smith drives this one past mid on and takes three more runs as Gill from mid off chases and pulls the ball back.
Shortish around off, coming in with the angle, Hazlewood sways away from it.
Floated on off, Smith skips down the track and chips this one to deep mid-wicket and collects two runs.
On off, Smith looks to reverse paddle this one but misses.
This time, connects his paddle scoop over the keeper's head for a couple.
Flatter around off, SS guides this one through short third man for one. Hazlewood on strike now.
Floated on off, worked through square leg. Josh wanted the single but Smith sent him back into his crease.
On off, tucked to the leg side. Safely negotiated by Josh.
FOUR! Extraordinary batting this by Smith. A short ball around off, Smith plays the tennis forehand kind of shot towards the mid-wicket area and gets himself another boundary. Moves to 128 now.
Length on middle, Smith tucks this one in the gap at depp square leg and comes back for a brace. Toying with the field here is Smith.
Back of a length on middle, comes back in a little. Smith looks to tuck it towards square leg, but gets hit on the pads. A loud 'NO' from Smith after that.

OUT! RUN OUT! Steven Smith is run out looking to turn the this single into this double. You can't take Jadeja on like that but he will be very happy with the knock that he has played. On a length and around off, Smith looked to push this one to the off side but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to the square leg region. They go for the single but Smith pushes for the double. Jadeja runs in and has a shy at the keeper's end and he hits bulls eye. The umpire wants to check this upstairs. Replays roll in and Smith is well short. AUSTRALIA END THEIR FIRST INNINGS WITH 338.
Rohit and India are underway! On a good length around leg, Rohit tickles this one to the fine leg region for a single.
On a good length outside off, Gill leaves it alone.
Another length delivery outside off, Gill, again is not interested in playing at this.
Down the leg side, Shubman hops and looks to tuck it away but misses. Paine collects it cleanly.
Back of a length and on off, Gill hops and blocks this one out.

FOUR! What a confident stroke! Just shows you what a good mental state he is in. A length delivery, outside off, Gill leans forward and punches this one through the mid off region and even though Pucovski gives it chase, he is not able to stop it from crossing the ropes.
Short of a length and on off, Rohit looks to work on this but he misses and gets hit high on the thigh pad.
On off, pushed to mid on.
Outside off, Sharma is not interested in playing at this.
Back of a length and on off, Sharma is solid in his defense.
Outside off, left alone.
Another length delivery on off, Sharma pushes this one to the mid off region.
Back of a length around off, Gill hops and defends it on the off side.
Length ball shaping away from Gill, outside off, he leaves that undisturbed.
Fuller length around off, enticing Gill for the drive, but he is firm in his leave.
On middle, Gill pushes that one through the covers and says a loud 'No' for the single.
Length outside off, Gill lets it go through to Paine.
Fuller ball outside off, Gill watches it closely and then shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! SHOT! A length ball around off, Rohit lets the ball come to him and then guides it through the gully region to collect his first boundary.
Length around off, Rohit plays that with soft hands towards gully. Green there dives to his left and saves runs for his team.
On a length around middle, Rohit tickles this towards deep square leg and comes back for the second easily. Nice start this by Rohit.
Back of a length around off, Rohit defends it on the on side.
Fuller this time outside off, Rohit lets it be.
Length around off, Rohit pushes this one towards point and takes off for a single, but returns as his partner says 'No'.
Shortish around middle, Gill defends it towards short leg.
Length ball around middle, Gill defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Excellent backfoot punch. A shortish ball outside off, Gill punches it through the covers off the backfoot and gets himself another boundary. Nice positive intent from Gill here.
Back of a length around middle, Gill defends it on the on side.
NO BALL AND FOUR! SHOT! Second boundary of the over. A short ball on middle, Gill rocks back and times his pull to perfection towards deep square leg. Starc has overstepped on this delivery.
Fuller around middle, Gill blocks this out on the off side.
Good running. A length ball around off, Gill prods forward and pushes it towards mid off and takes off for a quick single. Good over this for India and Gill.
On a good length on off, Gill nudges this one to the square leg region and picks up a single.
A full ball on middle, Rohit clips this one to the leg side but the fielder at square leg does not let the ball beat him.
Short of a length and on middle, pushed to the leg side.
A full ball on off, Rohit digs this one out to the leg side again.

FOUR! Something that you see Rohit do a lot in white ball cricket, but this time he does it against the red ball. A short ball, on middle, Sharma swivel-pulls this one to the deep square leg region and it crosses the ropes after a couple of bounces.
On off, Sharma looks to block this one out but the ball takes the outer half of the bat and goes towards the gully fielder, makes a good stop.
Patty starts off with a back of a length delivery around off, Gill looks to block this one but the ball nips back and hits him high on the thigh pad.
On a length outside off, Gill leaves it alone.
Another length delivery outside off, Shubman leaves this one nicely.
Well bowled and well blocked as well! A back of a length and around off, Gill blocks this one out.
Well fielded by Labuschagne at covers. A half-volley, waiting to be hit, outside off, Gill leans into the drive and punches this one towards covers where Marnus dives and stops the ball well.
On off, blocked out. A maiden to start off with by Hazlewood.
On a good length around off, Sharma covers his sticks and blocks this solidly.
A length ball outside off, Rohit shoulders arms to this one.
Length around off, Sharma shuffles and defends this one towards mid-wicket region.

BEATEN! What a ball. A length ball around off, straightens after pitching. Rohit looks to play at it but misses and the ball is collected cleanly by Paine. A huge appeal from Paine but no support from any of his teammates. Paine doesn't opt for the review. Rightly so as the replay show clear daylight between bat and ball.
Around off, Rohit solidly defends this towards the bowler.
On middle, Sharma blocks this out with a straight bat to the bowler.
Length around off, Gill pushes it towards covers.
Bumper now on middle and leg, Gill spots it early and ducks under that one.
Back of a length on off, Gill blocks this out back to Cummins.
Good length around off, Gill pushes this one to the off side.
Back of a length on middle, Gill shuffles and tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball around off, Gill prods forward and blocks it solidly towards covers. TEA ON DAY 2!

BEATEN! Lovelyyyyy! What a delivery from Josh, right after the Tea break! On a length and around off, moves away after taking the deck, Rohit is all squared up as he looks to block but he misses it altogether.
On a good length outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Angles in another length delivery around off, Rohit blocks this one out solidly off his front foot.
Length and on middle, RS pushes this one back towards Josh.

An appeal for LBW but turned down. A back of a length delivery around off and middle, nips back in after pitching, Rohit looks to play at this but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Looked to be way too high.
On off, pushed to covers.
Bumper on middle, Gill sits well under this one. Shubman has played these short balls well so far.
Back of a length on off, Gill keeps it out well.
Two this time. On a length and around off, Gill guides this through the gully region and the batters pick up two runs before the fielder can run in and stop this one.
Another length delivery around off, Gill pushes this one back towards Patty.
On off, SG works this to mid-wicket.
Lovely shot but for no runs. A length delivery, outside off, Gill punches this one to the left of Cummins, who fields this in his followthrough.
On off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Hazlewood goes for a bouncer this time on middle. Sharma ducks under this one well.
On off, RS works this to the leg side.
A back of a length and around off and middle, Sharma misses his stroke and the ball hits him high on the thigh pad. An appeal but no says the umpire.
Good length and around off, Sharma watchfully blocks this one out.
Similar ball as the last delivery. Again, Sharma is solid in his defense. Josh is testing Rohit here well.
On off, Gill defends this one out.
Another good stroke by Gill. Cummins dishes a back of a length ball outside off, Gill hops, gets on top of the bounce and slams this one through the cover region. Picks up two runs.
On off, blocked.

FOUR! CHEEEEEEKY! Wonderful stroke! Smart batting by the youngster! Kept his eyes on the ball till the last minute and then was brave enough to try this shot. Short of a length delivery outside off, Gill waits for it, opens up the face of the bat and steers this one through the backward point region to bag a boundary.
Bouncer on middle, SG knows what he has to do. Sits under this one.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Tossed up around off, Rohit blocks this off the front foot.
Similar ball around off, Rohit pushes it towards point.
Floated on off, Rohit is solid in his defense here.
Tossed up on middle, played back to the bowler.
Teasing around off, Rohit plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter this time, turns in around off, Rohit guides it towards point. Maiden to start by Lyon.
On off, Gill defends it towards covers.
Length ball around off, Gill plays it softly towards gully. The fielder ther dives to his left and saves runs for his team.

Close! A back of a length ball on off, Gill looks to defend but gets an inside edge on his pads. The ball starts lobbing towards the stumps, Gill does well to spot that and kick it out. Very nonchalantly done.
Length around off, pushed towards covers.
Good leave here by Gill. A length ball just outside off, tempting Gill to play at it, but he resists the temptation.
Back of a length on middle, Gill hops and defends it back towards Cummins. Good over this by Cummins here.
Floated outside off, spins back in after pitching, Sharma lunges forward and defends it out well.

SIX! WHAM! Enough of patience, says Sharma and he whacks this one for a biggie. Flighted and around off, Sharma skips down the track and gets to the pitch of the ball as well. Lofts it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Flatter and around off, Rohit tucks this one to square leg for a single.
On off, tucked to the leg side. 'Bowled, Gazzzzzza', says the skipper, Paine, from behind the stumps.
Loopy and around off, Sharma prods forward and pushes it to point.

FOUR! Deft placement and timing on this one will send it to the ropes! Floated on off, Sharma gets low and paddles this one through the short fine leg region and even though, Warner gives it a chase but the ball wins the race to the ropes.
Length ball outside off, Gill shoulders arms to that one.
On mddle and off, Gill is solid in his defense.
Cummins now bowls a bumper on middle and leg, Gill watchfully ducks under that.
Good length around off, bit of shape away, Gill pushes it towards covers.
Back of a length around off, Gill hops and pushes it towards covers for no run.
Fuller on middle and leg, Gill smartly flicks this in the gap between mid-wicket and mid on. They take two runs before the ball is returned back.
Tossed up around off, Rohit dead bats it in front of him.
Slower ball tossed up around off, Rohit is solid in his defense.
Floated on off, Rohit looks to come down and then looks to defend, but the ball hits the pads and goes towards covers.
Flatter around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
On off, Rohit prods forward and defends it.
Tossed up around off and bounces a little high as Rohit looks to block that one. Gets it off the inside edge and hits the pads.

Excellent backfoot punch. A shortish ball around off, Gill punches it off the backfoot through the covers for a brace. 50 up for India with that couple. 50 run-stand up as well between these two. A good partnership so far.
Length around off, Gill defends it off his front foot.
Angles in a length ball around off, Gill pushes this one towards covers.
Bumper now on middle and leg, Gill just sits under it.
Another one of those bumpers on middle, Gill just ducks under this one.
Fuller length around off, Gill prods forward and defends it to the off side solidly.
On off, blocked out.
Flighted and on off, tucked to the leg side.
Flighted delivery around off, Sharma prods forward and pads it away to the cover region. Looks for the single but does not take it.
On off, watchfully kept out.
Slower in the air and outside off, Rohit comes forward and blocks it out again.
Flatter and on off, RS goes on his back foot and pushes it back towards Lyon. A maiden by Nathan.
Fuller around middle, Gill plays it with a straight bat towards mid on.
Fuller length around off, Gill prods forward and then defends it solidly on the off side.
On middle and off, Gill watches it closely and then keeps it out.

Huge Appeal for caught behind but no review from Australia. A fuller length around off, jags back in sharply and then hits Gill on his pad through to Paine. Was very close to the bat, but a good decsion by the umpire and also a good call from Paine not to review it, as Snicko shows that this clipped the pad on the way through to Paine.
Length ball around middle, tucked on the leg side for no run.
Fullish ball outside off, Gill drives this beautifully but straight to covers.
Floated around off, Rohit tucks this towards square leg.
On off, Rohit turns this one towards short leg.
Fuller on middle, Rohit sweeps but it goes to hit Wade at short leg.
Floated around off, Rohit prods forward to defend but gets hit on the pads. Appeal from the Aussies but nothing from the umpire. Paine, again does not opt for the review.
Tossed up around off, Rohit sweeps this one towards deep square leg for a brace.
On middle, Rohit keeps this one out.
Fuller length around middle, Gill looks to drive but the ball goes on the inner part towards mid on.
FOUR! Pulled handsomely. A shortish ball on middle, Gill rocks back and pulls this one nonchalantly towards deep mid-wicket to get himself another boundary.
FIVE WIDES! A bumper on middle, Gill ducks under it. Paine behind the stumps jumps but fails to collect it and the ball races away to the fence. Also, wided by the umpire due to the height on this.
Fullish around off, Gill drives it straight to mid on.
Length around off, Gill defends it back to the bowler.
Around off, Gill prods forwards and pushes it towards covers.
Length around off, Gill watches that closely and plays it right under his eyes. He is looking good at the crease with every shot he plays.
Flighted delivery outside off, Sharma lunges front and blocks it out.
On off, Sharma worked this to the mid on region.
On off, Rohit looks to block but the ball takes the inner half of the blade and hits his pads.

NOT OUT! A very good review taken by Sharma and the on-field decision has been overturned. Lyon floats up a delivery around off, making Sharma come forward and looks to block it. To the naked eye, it looks like it has come off his pad and then onto his glove and then lobbed towards Wade at short leg. The players appeal and the umpire takes a second or two and then raises his finger. Sharma goes for the review. Ultra Edge comes in and there does not seem to be a spike. The third umpire has a look from a couple of different angles. Hot Spot is also in and there does not seem to be any contact of the ball with the glove. The third umpire deems to have enough evidence to overturn the decision and he does so. Rohit survives.
Flighted on off, Sharma punches this one to the cover region.
On off, blocked out.
Length around middle and off, Gill plays it towards covers.
On a length around middle, Gill defends this one off the backfoot.
Fuller length on off, tails in after pitching, Gill pushes it down towards mid off.
Length on middle and leg, tucked towards mid-wicket for no run.
A length ball around off, seams away after pitching, Gill guides it towards gully.
On middle, Gill tucks this one towards deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Lovely drive. A tossed up ball outside off, Gill prods forward and drives this one through the covers for his 6th boundary.
Floated on middle, Gill comes down and blocks it out.
Flatter on middle, Gill rocks on his back foot and blocks this out.
On middle, Gill tucks this towards mid-wicket but straight to the fielder.
Flatter around off, Gill defends this on the on side.
Slightly short on middle, Gill rocks back and pulls it through backward square leg region for a brace before the fielder returns the ball back.
A good length delivery around middle and leg, Sharma tickles this one to the fine leg region and will collect a couple of runs.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Good length around off, Sharma pushes this one to the cover region.

Some aggression from Hazlewood. On a length on off, Sharma plays this one nicely back towards the bowler and Josh just has a shy at the striker's end but he does not hit the target. Don't even think that he was aiming at the stumps.
Bumper on middle, left alone by the Hitman.

OUT! CAUGHT! A soft, soft dismissal and Sharma has just given Hazlewood a late New Year's present. It was all one way traffic until now but Josh has broken this promising stand. A very sharp catch by Josh. He bowls this on a length and around off, Sharma looks to drive this one past the bowler but does so slightly uppishly. It is enough for Hazlewood to get low to his left and grab this one out of thin air. The 70-run stand between these two comes to an end and the Aussies will be glad that they got a breakthrough.
FOUR! SHOT! A tossed up ball around off, Gill comes down the track and creams this one through the covers for a boundary. Into the 40s now, is Gill.
Floated on middle, Gill plays it back to the bowler.
Flat and around off, blocked out.
On middle, Gill defends it towards the bowler.
Shortish around middle, Gill tucks this one towards deep mid-wicket and changes ends.
Flatter around off, Pujara pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller length around off, Gill plays it towards covers.
FOUR! Brilliant shot! Short and wide outside off, Gill cuts it through cover-point region for a boundary. The fielder at deep point ran to his right and tried but could not cut it off.
Around middle, Gill defends this one on the leg side.
Length around middle, Gill tucks it towards mid-wicket and tries to steal a run, but returns back after Pujara says 'NO'.
