BEATEN! Lovely delivery from Cummins. A length ball around off, shapes away after pitching. Gill looks to defend that one but gets beaten all ends up.
Shortish around off, Gill pushes it through the covers and comes back for a couple before the fielder returns the ball back. Gill moves onto 49 now.
Floated on off, well kept out.
Outside off, turns back in sharply, Pujara leaves this one alone.
Loopy and on middle, CP blocks this one to the mid-wicket fielder.
Flat and on middle, Cheteshwar works this to the mid-wicket region.
Flatter outside off, Pujara looks to leave it alone but seeing that it is turning back in, he pads it away.
Short and on middle, Pujji gets off the mark and he works this through the mid-wicket region and picks up three runs.
On a good length around off, nipping back in, Pujara, as always, is good in his defensive push away.
Full ball on middle, CP pushes this to the cover region this time.
Good leave by Chesteshwar. On a length outside off, Pujara raises his blade and lets this one through to the keeper.
On off, blocked.
Back of a length and on middle, Pujara tucks this one to the backward square leg region. Wade, who was at leg gully, runs to his left, dives and stops the ball.

BEATEN. Ohhh...Patty, you beauty. Doing his thing with the ball in hand. Outside off, on a length, straightens after taking the deck, Pujara's attempt to block this out does not work out as the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Flatter and on off, Gill plays it back to Nathan.
Floated on off, Gill blocks this one out. 'BOWLED, NATHANNNN', says Paine. Follows it up with a 'BEAUTIFUL GAZZZZ'. The skipper is cheering his bowlers on here.

FIFTY FOR SHUBMAN GILL. A well deserved one by Gill. He has batted really well and will want to continue the same. Shortish and on middle, worked to the square leg region and the batters complete the run.
On off, blocked.
On middle, flicked to the square leg region.
Flat and on off, CP defends.

OUT! CAUGHT! A good innings by Gill but unfortunately for him, it comes to an end. It has been a controlled innings by him so far but all it takes is one ball from someone of Cummins' caliber to send him packing. A fine catch by Green as well. Cummins darts in a good length delivery around the off pole, the ball moves away ever so slightly after taking the deck, Gill look to block this one but the ball takes the outside edge and flies towards the gully fielder and Green, there, gets low and takes a delightful catch.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Some extra bounce this time. A back of a length ball on middle and leg, Rahane looks to defend but the bounce gets slightly big on him and the ball hits Rahane on his thigh pad.
Rahane is off the mark here. On a length and on middle, clipped to fine leg for a single.
Well bowled by Cummins. Again, outside off, on a good length, seams away from the right-hander as Pujji misses his block. Testing the batters, is Cummins.
On off, blocked out.
Floated on off, Rahane pushes this away off the back foot.
Outside off, Rahane prods forward and looks to block but misses and the ball hits him on the pads.
On off, kept out.
Shorter and around off, Jinks gets on his back foot and defends this to the mid on region.
On off, AR blocks it out again.
Loops it up nicely around off, Rahane defends it out well. A maiden by Lyon.
Fullish around off, Pujara prods forward to defend but gets it on the inner half of the bat and goes on the leg side.
On off, Pujara blocks this one solidly under his eyes.
Length around middle, Pujara plays it towards square leg.
Back of a length around middle, Pujara defends this out off the backfoot.
A length ball just outside off, comes back in as it passes the stumps, Pujara lets it go through to Paine.
Shortish length around off, Pujara looks to defend but the ball bounces and hits him high on his gloves. Good over this by Cummins. Gets another maiden.
Floated around off, Rahane defends this one towards Lyon.
On off, Rahane defends this off the back foot.
Flatter around off, Rahane blocks this out towards short leg.
Slower tossed up ball on middle, Rahane prods forwards and defends.

Slighly short on off, Rahane looks to tuck but misses and gets hit on the pads and the ball lobs towards short leg. Shouts of 'catch it' but the ball drops short of the fielder at short leg. There was some bat there. Lucky escape this for Rahane.
On middle, Rahane keeps this out.
Length ball in the channel outside off, Cheteshwar lets it go.
Fuller ball around off, Pujara pushes this one towards covers. Tight lines these by Cummins.
Short ball now on middle and leg, Pujara sits under it.
Length ball around off, Pujara looks to defend that one but the ball keeps low and Pujara somehow manages to block that.
Length around off, Pujara stands tall and plays it back to the bowler.
Fuller around off, Pujara plays that one softly towards point. Maiden over by Cummins.
Floated around middle, Rahane defends that one off his front foot.
Tossed up around off, Rahane comes down the track and drives it straight to mid off.
Slightly shortish around off, Rahane punches that one through cover-point for a brace.
On middle, Rahane defends this on the on side.
Floated around off, Rahane looks to defend but the ball keeps low and he somehow manages to block that out.
Fullish around middle, Rahane prods forward and defends this one out.
Angles in a length delivery around off, Pujara blocks this one out.
Good length delivery outside off, Pujara is well aware of his sticks as he raises his bat to let this one through to Tim.
Outside off, well left again by Pujji. What a patient man, he is.
On middle, clipped to the square leg region.
Full ball on off, Pujara pushes this one to the cover region.
On off, Pujara plays it back towards Starc.
Loopy on off, Rahane whips this one towards mid on but says no to the single.
On off, blocked out solidly.
Flighted outside off, Rahane defends this one out off his front foot.

NOT OUT! Rahane survives! It is Umpire's Call on the wickets. Floated on off, Rahane prods forward and looks to pad it away and does so. A loud appeal and no says the umpire. Paine has a talk with several teammates and then at the end moment, he decides to go for the review. The umpires have a chat, as to what whether Rahane deliberately padded the ball away. They decide that no shot was offered to this delivery. Ball Tracker comes in and it is Umpire's Call on wickets. Rahane will not be out and the on-field decision stays on.
On middle, defended.
On middle, worked to square leg for a single.
A shortish ball angling across, Rahane looks to play at it, but sways away at the last moment as it goes through to the keeper.
Shortish on the body, Rahane works this one towards fine leg for a run.
Shortish outside off stump, Pujara lets it go through to the keeper.
Length ball around off, Pujara defends this one towards mid-wicket.
On off, Pujara just blocks this out solidly on the on side.
Fullish ball on off, Pujara pushes this one to the left of the cover fielder and takes three more. Labuschagne there chases the ball and saves a run for his team.
Floated on middle, Pujara dances down the deck and flicks this one slightly uppish through the mid-wicket region and picks up three runs as Starc chases and stops this one.
On off, blocked out.
Flatter and on off, kept out by Jinks.
Short and on off, AR tucks this to the square leg region.
Similar delivery as the last one, tapped to the cover-point region.
Short and on off again, nudged to the fielder at short leg.
Shortish on the pads, Pujara tucks this one towards square leg.
Back of a length around middle, Pujara nudges this one through to square leg for no run.
Fuller length around middle, Pujara covers his sticks and defends this out on the on side.
Bumper now on middle, Pujara just sits under this one.
Length ball around middle, Pujara plays it towards short leg.
Shortish ball down the leg side, Pujara sways away from the line and lets it go through to the keeper. Good over this by Starc.
Floated on middle, Rahane blocks this out off the front foot.
On middle, Rahane plays it down towards short leg.
Flatter around off, Rahane blocks this out on the off side.
Slightly short on off, Rahane plays this back to Lyon.
Floated around off, comes back in sharply, Rahane manages to block that in time.
Floated on middle, Rahane keeps this out.
Shortish outside off, Pujara lets it go through to Paine.
Fuller this time around off, Pujara defends this out back towards the bowler.
Shortish again angling across the off pole, Pujara just sways away from the line and lets it go through.
Shortish around off, Pujara stands tall and blocks this out.
Short ball on the body, Pujara is happy swaying away from it and letting it go through to Paine.
Short and outside off, Pujara lets it go. With that, it's STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Lyon tosses the first ball around off, Rahane comes on the front foot to block.
Rahane and India are up and running on Day 3. A fuller ball on middle, Rahane flicks it down to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Pujara is underway too! A flatter ball around off, Pujara goes back and punches it through covers for a brace.
Floats this one around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Another single! Shortish and just outside off, it is cut wide of the man at gully. 100 up for the Indians.
Flatter and around off, punched towards mid off for nothing. 4 off the first over of Day 3.
Good length and around off, Pujara defends.
Fullish and just around off, Pujara is on the front foot to block.
Very full and around off and middle, watchfully kept out by Pujara.
Full again, this one is played to the left of mid-wicket. Pujara wants a single but Rahane says no.
Shortish and around off, Pujara punches it towards point.
A maiden from Cummins to begin his spell. A length ball around middle, Pujara works it towards mid-wicket.
Good length and around off and middle, pushed to mid on.
A sharp bumper from Starc. Rahane looks to pull but opts against it at the last moment.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Length ball around off, pushed towards cover-point.
Fuller and on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for one.
Shortish and just outside off, poked to point by Pujara. Just a run from Starc's first over.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Length ball around off, tucked towards short leg.
Length and around off, kept out.
A bouncer aimed at the head. Rahane does well to evade it.
Length and around off, flicked to square leg.
Another maiden from Cummins. A good length ball around off, it shoots up extra as Rahane takes one hand off the handle to block.
Fullish and just outside off, pushed towards point.
A bouncer to Pujara from Starc. Pujara ducks under it.
Short ball around middle, turned towards square leg.
Shortish and down the leg side. Pujara looks to flick but misses.
Short again but outside off, left alone.
Another bouncer but this one is down the leg side. Pujara has no problems sitting under it.
Length on middle, Rahane works this one towards deep square for a run. First run off Cummins this morning.
Bumper around middle and off, Pujara ducks and lets it go through.
Length around off, Pujara defends this out off his front foot.
Back of a length around off, Pujara defends this one solidly.
Length around off, Pujara looks to play towards point but gets an inside edge on his pads.
Shortish length around off, turned towards square leg for no run.
FOUR! Classy drive. A fuller length around off, Rahane transfers his weight on the front foot and drives this one through the covers for a boundary.
Length around off, Rahane hops and plays it towards covers.
Shortish around middle and leg, Rahane turns this one towards short leg.
Shortish on middle again, Rahane hops and defends this one awkwardly on the pitch.
Length on off, pushed towards point.
Short again around off, Rahane swivels and pulls this one towards fine leg for a run.
Fullish on middle, flicked towards deep square leg for a brace.
Short around off, Rahane pulls this one towards fine leg and changes ends.
Shortish around middle, Pujara blocks this out on the leg side.
Shortish again on the pads, Pujara tucks this towards square leg for no run.
Good ball this by Cummins. Short around off, Pujara drops his hands and lets it go through to Paine. Good leave this by Pujara as he watched the ball closely and then dropped his wrists.
Back of a length to finish around off, Pujara plays it on the off side.
Shortish around off, pushed towards covers.
Flatter around off, Rahane works this one towards square leg.
Floated outside off, Rahane prods forwards and blocks this one.

Was that a chance? Yes, it was and Wade cannot hold on. A big inside edge. Lyon tosses it up and around off, Rahane looks to defend but it spins in. Takes the inside edge, hits the pad and lobs over short leg. Wade there flings himself behind to take the catch but only manages to get fingertip to it.
Shortish and around off, punched towards cover.
SIX! WOW! That is some response from Rahane. A tossed up ball around off, Rahane jumps out of the crease and deposits it over long on for a biggie. Shot of authority from Rahane.
Shortish around middle, Pujara clips this one towards square leg. Thinks for a run but returns back.
Short ball on the body, Pujara just bends down and lets it go.
Good running. Fullish ball on middle, Pujara pushes this one towards mid on for a single.

OUT! Dragged on! Big, big wicket. The one the Aussies dearly wanted. A shortish ball around off, this one comes back in a touch as Rahane looks to run it down towards third man. However, he ends up getting a big inside edge which goes onto the shatter the stumps. That kept low. Rahane cannot believe what has happened there. Massive, massive moment in the game. The dropped chance doesn't cost Australia much and the centurion from the last game has been removed. He was starting to look positive there but Cummins gets the better of him.
Bouncer to welcome Vihari. On middle, Vihari ducks under it.
Back of a length on off, Vihari blocks this out. Successful over from Cummins.
Floated around off, turns back in sharply, Pujara looks to turn that one. It goes in the air towards leg slip area where luckily for Pujara, there is no fielder there.
Floated on middle, turns this on on the leg side.

NOT OUT! Nothing on Hot Spot and Snicko. Pujara survives. Lyon floats it fullish and on middle and leg, Pujara looks to defend but it spins in. The ball lobs towards short leg after hitting the pad. Wade takes the catch and the Aussies appeal. Not out says the umpire. Paine has a word with the bowler and then he goes for the review. Replays roll in and they show that there is no bat involved, as confirmed by the Hot Spot and Snicko. They check for LBW too. Ball Tracker shows that the ball would've missed the leg pole. So, Pujara is safe. Australia lose one of their reviews.
Flatter and around middle, turned towards square leg.
Flat and around off, pushed to the right of the bowler.
Full and outside off, poked towards short third man for one. End of a probing over from Lyon.
Hazlewood starts with a length ball on middle, Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
In the channel outside off, Pujara is happy leaving that one.
Fullish around off, Pujara comes forward and defends this one on the pitch.
Similar ball around off, Pujara is solid in his front foot defense.
Length ball outside off, comes back in a little, left alone by Pujara.
Maiden over from Hazlewood. Finishes the over with a bouncer, Pujara sways and ducks under it.
Tossed up outside off, played back to Lyon.
Floated around middle and leg, Vihari turns this one towards square leg.
On off, Vihari plays it on the on side.
Floated around off, turned away towards short leg.
Fullish around off, worked away towards mid-wicket.
On middle and leg, tucked towards short fine leg.
Length ball around off, Pujara just defends it back towards the bowler.
Fullish around middle and leg, Pujara flicks this one towards deep square leg for a brace before the fine leg fielder throws it back to the keeper.
Short ball on the body, Pujara ducks under this one.
Fullish length on middle, Pujara watches it closely and blocks it out.
Short again on the body, Pujara sits under it.
Fuller around off, pushed towards point. Good probing over this by Hazlewood.
Flatter and around off, pushed to mid on off the back foot.
Fuller and around off, bunted on the leg side.
Loopy and just around off, defended.
Looped up on middle, turning in. Vihari lets it be.
Vihari is off the mark. Fuller and around off, pushed towards cover for a single.

Dropped? Not sure. Tossed up and outside off, Pujara comes down the track and looks to play but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball lobs wide of the man at silly point who tries to catch but misses.
Fullish around off, Vihari lets this one go through to Paine. A hint of reverse as the ball passes the stumps.
Length around middle, Vihari flicks this one towards square leg. The fielder dives to his right and stops the single.
Length on middle, turned away towards short leg.
A bumper now around off, Vihari sits under this one.
In the channel outside off, shouldered arms by Vihari.
Fuller around off, pushed towards covers. Vihari looks for a single but Pujara says a loud 'NO'. Another maiden from Hazlewood.

FOUR! Signs of aggression from Pujara. A fuller ball around off, Pujara dances down the track and nails the drive through mid on. The fielder gives it a chase, dives but fails to cut it off. First boundary for Pujara and it comes on the 101st ball of his innings.
On off, Pujara defends it.
FOUR! Slapped away! More aggression. Lyon drops it short and gives enough room for Pujara to slam it through the cover region for another boundary. He is putting pressure here on Lyon.

Three now! Excellent running. Floated outside off, Pujara flicks it through square leg. They take two but Pujara wants three. Vihari is slow in taking off for the thrid one but the throw from Starc isn't that great. So, they make it easiy in the end. Excellent from Pujara in this over.
Looped up and around off, kept out.
Full and around off, flicked to mid on for nothing. 11 off the over. A good one for the Indians.
Fuller on middle, Pujara watches and blocks this out.
Fuller length again on middle, Pujara defends this one solidly.
Length on middle, clipped towards square leg for no run.
Short but down the leg, Pujara gets away from the line and lets it go through to Paine.
Fullish around middle, Pujara turns this one towards mid-wicket.
Fullish around middle, Pujara blocks this out. 3rd consecutive maiden from Hazlewood.
Tossed up around off, played straight back to Lyon.
Floated around off, Vihari works this on the leg side.
Floated around middle and leg, Vihari flicks this one fine towards fine leg area and comes back for a couple.
On off, defended on the leg side.

Chance again! Around off, Vihari looks to defend on the leg side, gets an inside edge on his pads and the ball lobs over Wade at short leg. He jumps and tries to take that but couldn't take it. 2nd chance gone down at short leg this morning.
Loopy and around off, Vihari this time comes on the front foot and blocks.
Fuller and around off, blocked.
FOUR! SHOT! Another boundary for Pujara. He is turning things around here. A fullish ball around off, Pujara punches it down the ground and it races away to the fence.
Gets back to blocking the ball. It is once again full and on middle, Pujara bocks it back to Josh.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked towards the leg side.
On the pads, Pujara looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad.
A length ball on the pads, Pujara tries to flick but misses. A bit of appeal from Paine but nothing from the umpire.
Tossed up around off, pushed towards mid on.
Around off, Vihari blocks this out on the on side.
Tossed up outside off, tucked towards short leg.
Short and around off, punched wide of mid off for a single.
Full and around off, Pujara comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket for two more.
He flicks again but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Short ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
Fuller length around off, Vihari defends this out solidly.
Length ball drifting down leg, clipped towards leg gully. The fielder does well to stop the ball.
Bumper now on middle and leg, Vihari ducks under it.
Back of a length around off, Vihari defends this one towards short leg.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards covers.
Tossed up outside off, Pujara comes down and works this towards mid on for a quick single.

OUT! RUN OUT! Vihari is short. Stunning work from Hazlewood. A fuller ball just outside off, Vihari jumps out of his crease and pushes it wide of the man at mid off. He calls for the single straightaway and Pujara responds. Hazlewood from mid off dives to his right, stops the ball and hits the stumps at the non-striker's end, did that all in one motion. The Aussies celebrate. The third umpire has been called for and one replay is enough to send Vihari packing. His stay in the middle has been cut short, because of some stunning work from the big Josh.
Tossed up around off, Pujara comes down the track and pads this one away on the off side.
On middle, punched down the ground.
Flatter and around off, punched back to Lyon.
Looped up and around off, played back to the bowler again. End of a successful over for Australia.
A full toss around off to begin, Pant punches it towards mid on.
Pant is underway! Good length and just around off, Pant opens the bat face and guides it wide of backward point. Two taken.
Short and around off, poked towards point.
Length ball around off, punched towards mid off.
Sharp bouncer around off, Pant sways away from the line. Starc has an advice or two for Pant there.
Good response from Pant. Shortish and just around off, Pant punches it through covers and bags a brace.
Fired it fuller and outside off, Pujara pads it away.
Flat and just outside off, punched towards cover for a single.

FOUR! That's how Pant plays. He is not going to just keep blocking and blocking. Just a fraction short and a bit of room too. Pant slams it through point and it races away to the fence. 150 up for the Indians.
Smartly pushes the next fuller one towards covers for a single.
Pujara rotates strike as his jumps out of his crease and flicks it wide of the man at mid on. A diving stop there but a single is taken.
Floated outside off, pushed towards cover. 7 off the over.
Back of a length on off, Pujara is solid in his defense here.
Shortish around middle, Pujara tucks this away towards square leg.
Fuller this time around middle, kept out by Pujara.
Length and outside off, Pujara lets it go through to Paine.
Length around off, Pujara pushes this one to point.
Fuller this time outside off, Pujara is not interested in playing the drive there. Left alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller around off, Pant defends this one on the off side.
Looped on middle, played back to Lyon.
Fired outside off, left alone.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep point for one.
FOUR! Super shot from Pujara. Short and just outside off, Pujara rocks back and punches it through covers. It races away to the fence. Pujara on 40 now.
Fuller length outside off, Pant drives this one in the gap at cover-point and comes back for a couple before the fielder there returns the ball.
Shortish on the body, Pant tucks this one towards fine leg for a run.
LEG BYE! A shortish ball on the body, drifting down leg, Pujara tries to sway away from that but the ball hits the elbow guard and goes towards fine leg. The batsmen cross over for a leg bye.
Lovely bouncer from Starc. It is on middle and leg, Pant takes his eyes off and looks to fend it off. The ball takes the gloves and lobs up. It goes down to fine leg for one.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Good length and around off, Pujara is on his toes to block.

NOT OUT! There is nothing on Hot Spot and nothing on Snicko either. A rank long hop down the leg side. Pant goes for the pull but misses. Paine moves to his right and catches it. He appeals but not out says the umpire. Paine has a word with the bowler and then he goes for the review. Replays roll in and it confirms that the onfield call is a correct one. Australia lose another review.

FOUR! Pant goes after Labuschagne straightaway. A tossed up ball coming into Pant, he sits down and slogs this one towards deep mid-wicket to collect a boundary. Pant will not let the part time spinner settle down here.
On middle, clipped towards short fine leg for one.
On off, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and wide outside off, Pujara nails the drive but finds the cover fielder.
Length ball around off, Pant defends this one towards covers.
Length around off, pushed towards point.
FOUR! CUTS AND CUTS HARD! A short ball outside off, Pant hops and cuts this fiercely towards third man for a boundary. Pant looking good here.
A perfect response from Starc now. A bouncer on middle and leg, Pant sways away from it.
Another bumper around off, Pant leaves that alone.
Shortish around middle, Pant hops and tucks this one past the short leg fielder towards deep square for a single. It was really close to the fielder there at short leg. A run taken in the end.
Short ball around off, Pant pulls it hard but the ball hits the short leg fielder.
Friendly full toss, pushed down to long on for one.
Full and outside off, Pujara hits it hard to the right of the cover fielder. A half stop and they take a single.
Pant tucks it through mid-wicket now and takes one.
This one is fired outside off, it turns away as Pujara lets it be. Paine cannot stop it but Smith at first slip does well to stop the ball to his left.
This is again outside off, Pujara is not interested.
Green starts with a length ball outside off, Pant lets it go through to Paine.
Length around middle and leg, Pant looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Appeal from the bowler but the umpire is unmoved. The ball was pitching outside leg as shown by the replays.
Bouncer now on middle, Pant ducks under this one.
Length around off, Pant pushes it on the off side.
A length around off, Pant plays it straight to point.
Good running this by Pant. A length ball on off, Pant softly plays it towards covers and calls his partner for a quick run to keep strike.
Shortish and down the leg side. Left alone by Pant.
Tossed up and around off, kept out.
Full and on middle, it is pushed down to long on for one.
Short and just outside off, punched to the left of the cover fielder for one.
Another single as Pant works this short ball on the leg side.
Outside off, left alone by Pujara.
Length ball outside off, Pant shoulders arms to it.
Again a length ball outside off, Pant is not interested in playing that.
A shortish ball just around off, Pant leaves that one. The ball however passes very close to his helmet.
Length on off, Pant defends this one towards gully.
Good length ball outside off, Pant lets it go through to Paine.
A short ball on middle and leg, Pant easily sits under it. With that it's LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Floated outside off, Pujara pads it away.
Fuller anound middle, kept out.
Flat and around off, Pujara stays back to block.
Full and on middle, flicked to square leg.
On middle, played towards mid-wicket by Pujara.
Floated around off, tucked away towards square leg for a run to keep strike. 1 run from Lyon's first over after Lunch.
Two for Pujara. A fuller ball around middle and leg, swinging in, Pujara flicks it through square leg for a brace.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Short and down the leg side, Pujara lets it be.
Full again, pushed to mid on.
Length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms.
Outside off again, left alone.
Length ball around off, Pant looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, driven well but straight to the cover fielder.
Fuller and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Squirts it away! Shortish and just outside off, Pant goes on the back foot and looks to cut. Ends up chopping it through gully for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one in the channel outside off, Pant offers no shot again.
Wayward. This is way outside off on a good length. Pujara lets it go.
Starc pitches it up and it was just outside off, Pujara wanted to have a go at it but controlled his emotions and pulled his bat away. Good leave because it was angled away.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
A bumper on middle and leg, Pujara sits under it.
Length ball around off and middle, pushed to mid on.
Beaten! Lovely ball to end the over. Shortish and around middle and off, angling away. Pujara pokes at it. Only to get beaten.
Fuller and outside off, stroked through cover-point for one.

Pujara is beaten again. A superb ball from Josh. This is just outside off, Pujara looks to defend but is beaten as the ball first comes in and then straightens. Didn't go chasing and hence no edge there.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Good length and around off, Pujara is solid in defense.
Short and just outside off, Pujara sways away.
Length ball around off, Pant is on the front foot to block.
Very full and around off, digged out to mid on.
Play and a miss! A fuller ball just outside off, Pant looks to drive on the up but the ball beats his outside edge.
This one is angled in from a length on middle, Pant looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad.

Short and around off, Pant look to pull but misses to get hit on the arm. Pant is looking in some pain here. No elbow guard and he is hit flush on his left elbow. Didn't bounce as much as Pant expected it to be.
It is the short ball but Pant is pant. He goes hard at it and pulls it nicely. The deep square leg fielder does well to stop. A single taken.
Beaten! Length ball outside off, Pant looks to drive away from his body. Only to get beaten.
This time he lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish and around off and middle, Pant blocks off his toes.
Fullish and just outside off, driven to mid off.
Around off on a good length, Pant blocks.
Another solid defense from Pant as Josh bowls it around off on a length.
In the channel outside off, Pujara leaves that one.
Ouch! Short ball on the body. Pujara looks to duck but gets hit flush on his left shoulder.

FOUR! Nicely done from Pujara. A fuller ball just outside off, he comes on the front foot and then opens the bat face. It goes between second slip and gully. It races away to the fence. He moves to 49. The boundary brings up 50-run stand between the two. A valuable stand.
On a length around middle, Pujara clips this one towards mid-wicket.
Length on middle, Pujara plays it towards mid-wicket.
A bumper coming in with the angle, Pujara sways away slighlty and evades the ball.
Shortish around middle, Pant hops and defends this one on the leg side uncomfortably but runs a quick run to give Pujara the strike.

FIFTY FOR PUJARA! This has been one fighting knock from him. Maybe he has been a little too cautious but that's how he bats and goes about the business. He tires the opposition down and then starts scoring. That's exactly how he has done here. He hit his first boundary of the innings after playing 100 balls. And after that, it hasn't been that difficult for him. He gets to the milestone by flicking the fuller ball around off towards mid-wicket for one. This is his 26th in Tests and slowest of his career.
Fuller around off, Pant pushes this one towards covers.

OUT! TAKEN! Pant's stay has been cut short. Hazlewood is the man who strikes. A fuller ball outside off, Pant without any feet movement goes for the drive but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes to Warner at first slip. It goes quickly to him but he reacts sharply and holds onto it. Great take from the southpaw. Not from the one with the bat though as it was way outside off and he could've had easily left it alone. A start thrown away again by Pant.
A short ball to welcome Jadeja at the crease. Jadeja lets it go through. Stares exchanged and in the end, smiles.
Fuller ball around off, Jadeja prods forward and defends this out.
Back of a length and down the leg side. Left alone.

OUT! GONE! Huge wicket. Cummins is the man who has done it again. Big, big wicket. Excellent from Cummins. Good length and around off, it shoots off a touch after pitching. Pujara is glued in his crease as he pokes at it. The ball takes the gloves and goes behind. Paine is not going to miss out. A simple catch for him and he gobbles it. The battling knock from Pujara comes to an end and that leaves India in a massive trouble. They are still 143 behind.
A bouncer to welcome Ashwin. He sits under it.
Beaten! This is brilliant from Cummins. Ashwin is beaten all ends up. A length ball just around off, Ashwin pokes at it but the ball goes away ever so slightly and goes past the outside edge.
Fullish and just outside off, poked towards gully. Ashwin wants a single but Green makes a diving stop. Ashwin returns as Green has a shy at the striker's end. He hits but Ashwin was back.
Good length and around middle, kept out. End of a successful over from Cummins.
Misfield and a single. Jadeja is away. Fuller and around off, it is pushed straight to Starc at covers. He fumbles and Jadeja sneaks a run.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off.
Banged short and on middle and leg, Ashwin ducks.
FOUR! Ashwin is off the mark in style. A fuller ball outside off, Ashwin leans into the stroke and drives it through the covers. Fine shot to bring 200 up.
And it is the bouncer from Josh. Ashwin somehow manages to keep it down.
Good from Ashwin. A shortish ball around middle, he clips it behind square on the leg side for two.
Fullish ball on off, Jadeja does well to block this out.
Length ball around middle, Jadeja plays it softly towards point and takes off for a run, but returns back as Ashwin says 'NO'.
A bouncer now on middle and leg, Jadeja sits under this one.
Fullish ball around middle, Jadeja flicks this one towards mid-wicket and yells a loud 'NO'.
Short again on the body, Jadeja watches it closely and sways away from it.
Length around middle, Jadeja defends this one towards mid on. A maiden to start from Cummins after the break.
Floated around off, Ashwin blocks this out.
FOUR! Nicely played. a tossed up ball outside off, Ashwin comes down and drills this one down the ground past mid off for his second boundary.
On middle, turned towards mid-wicket.
Flatter and around off, Ashwin stays back to defend.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards point.
Tossed up and around off, Ashwin is on the front foot to block.
Length ball in the channel outside off, left alone by Jadeja.

OUT! RUN OUT! Ashwin is short. Poor, poor running from him. A fullish ball outside off, Jadeja drives this to the left of fielder at mid off and takes off for the run. Ashwin is slow to react to it. Cummins from mid off throws the ball to Marnus Labuschagne at the striker's end and he whips off the bails before Ashwin can make his ground. Third umpire has been called and the replays show Ashwin short by some margin. Waste of a wicket this by Ashwin. Second run out of the innings this. India 7 down now.
And he is welcomed with a sharp bumper. Saini sits under it.

First runs for Saini in Test match cricket. Well, not really. Given leg byes. Fuller and on the pads, Saini looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes towards short fine leg and they take a leg run. Looked like there was some bat but no. Given leg byes.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
In the channel outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Floated around off, Saini comes on the front foot to block.
Flat and around off, pushed towards cover.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Around off, turning in from a shortish length, Saini goes deep in his crease and bunts it onto the pitch on the leg side. Looking solid in defense.
Full this time and he hits it nicely but straight to Lyon.
Flat and around off, poked to mid off for a single.
Runs in and bangs it short but this is down the leg side.
Length ball around off, he punches it through covers and takes two.
Sharp bouncer! Saini looks to defend but it lobs up off the handle towards the off side.
Another short ball. Saini somehow manages to fend it off on the off side. Could've gone in the hands but Saini survives. Starc smiles.

OUT! TAKEN! Starc gets the wicket with that short ball tactics. Smart from Paine to bring him back. Not that smart from Jadeja to expose Saini for entire six balls against Starc. Another short ball around off and middle, Saini is hopping to fend it away. This time the Aussies brought a man at silly point. The ball hits the upper part of the bat and it goes to Wade. Wade is not dropping this. Perfectly planned wicket.
And he too gets welcomed with a bumper. Does well to get down.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and just outside off, Jadeja cuts it through backward point and it races away to the fence.
Tossed up and around off, pushed towards cover.
Fuller on middle, Jadeja blocks this out.
Flatter around off, played towards short third man.
Floated on middle, Jadeja turnes this one towards deep mid-wicket and takes a run.  Bumrah thinks for a second, but Jadeja sends him back.
Tossed up around off. Bumrah prods forwards and blocks this one.
Short and angling away from Jadeja, he lets it be.
Short again this time on leg, Jadeja thinks for the pull but ducks under it.

OUT! RUN OUT! 3rd run out of the innings. Jadeja clips this fuller ball towards deep square leg and immediately calls for two. The fielder from short leg, Labuschagne chases the ball down and scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end. Third umpire has been called for and replays show that Bumrah is well short there and has to make his way back to the pavilion. Australia have been excellent in the field especially with the direct hits. India 9 down now.
Shortish and around middle, Jadeja goes for the pull but this one keeps low and Jadeja misses. An appeal from behind the wickets from Paine but turned down.
FOUR! Useful boundary. Full and around off, Jadeja nails it through mid on for a boundary. Starc has overstepped too.

EDGED AND FOUR! Welcome runs! Fuller and outside off, Jadeja goes for a big slog again. The ball though takes the bottom edge and goes behind. Paine dives to his right and tries to stop but the ball evades him and goes to the fence.
A bouncer outside off. Jadeja cannot do much about it as he watches it go behind. Siraj will be on strike for the next over.
And he bangs it short first up. Siraj ducks under it.
Pitched up and outside off, Siraj looks to drive but misses.
Another bouncer! Goes over the ducking batter.
Siraj is underway! Fuller and around middle, he pushes it through mid on and gets a brace.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and wide outside off, Siraj cuts it through backward point and finds the fence.
Bangs it short and it goes well over Siraj. The last ball at the no. 11 is a wasted one from Green.

FOUR! Enough of ducking says Jadeja. A short ball on middle, Jadeja goes for the pull, gets a top edge which runs away towards the boundary at fine leg area. It bounces well ahead of the ropes but nonetheless a boundary for Jadeja.

IN THE AIR ..AND SAFE!! A length on middle, Jadeja again goes for the slog, gets the top edge this time again behind the keeper. The fielder from third man tries to catch the ball but the ball lands short of him and Jadeja takes a quick couple of runs before the fielder returns the ball back to Paine. Useful runs these for India.
Two more! Fuller and outside off, Jadeja strokes it through covers and scampers back for a couple. The lead is under 100 now.
Back of a length and on middle, kept out.

Dropped? Yes. But that was a hit really hard chance. A length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja flicks it uppishly. Labuschagne at short leg responds quickly and throws his right hand. The ball hits his palm but goes out.
A single and Jadeja will keep the strike. Banged short and outside off, Jadeja stays back and guides it over the slip cordon. The third man fielder makes a diving stop to his right.

Length outside off, Jadeja throws his hands at it and the ball races away fine towards third man area. The fielder there does well to stop the ball and throws it back. Jadeja refuses to take the single.
Shorter around middle and off, Jadeja lets it be.
Play and a miss! A length ball outside off, Jadeja goes for the slash but misses the ball altogether.
Shortish on middle, Jadeja hops and somehow manages to keep it down.

Shortish around middle, Jadeja plays it towards mid-wicket. Siraj at the non-striker's end looks to steal the run, but is sent back. The fielder has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. Had that hit, Siraj was a goner.

FOUR! Slammed away. Shortish around off, Jadeja pulls this one behind square and finds the gap at deep square leg area. Gets a boundary on the last ball of the over, which means Siraj will be on strike the next over.
A bouncer just around off, Siraj ducks under it. In fact he was down before Cummins released the ball.
Banged short and just outside off, Siraj backs away and then tries to poke at it. Misses.
Cummins bangs it short again. Siraj ducks well again. Three more balls for him to survive. Will Cummins dish out a fuller one now?

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! There is a spike as the ball gets closer to the bat, as shown by the Snicko. After banging three short, Cummins bowls a length ball just outside off, Siraj pokes at it without moving his feet. He ends up nicking it behind and the Aussies celebrate.The finger goes up but Siraj signals the 'T'. Replays roll in and they show a big spike on the Snicko. So, the onfield call will stay. India are bowled out for 244.
LEG BYE! A length ball on the pads, Warner looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball runs towards fine leg as they sneak a leg bye to start off the proceedings for Australia.
Length ball outside off, Will lets it go.
In the channel outside off, Pucovski is not interested in playing that.
Fuller this time around off, Will pushes this one towards cover-point.
Length on off, Will defends this towards covers.

FOUR! Shot! A shortish ball outside off, Pucovski pulls this one behind square and gets his first boundary of the innings. He was ready for the short ball and pulled it nicely in the gap at deep square leg region.
Length around off, Warner defends this on towards mid off.
Similar length around middle, Warner hops and defends this out.
Another one on middle, Warner blocks this out.
Fulish on middle, Warner prods forward and defends this with a straight bat.

BEATEN! Lovely ball from Siraj. Pitches on a length around off, straightens as it goes past Warner's tentative push. Misses the outside edge by not much and goes through to Saha. There is still something in the pitch for the fast bowlers.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards cover. A fine over from Siraj first up. A maiden.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Another good length and around off, Will is solid in defense.
FOUR! SHOT! Second boundary for Pucovski. Short and wide outside off, Pucovski slams it through the cover region and it races away. The Aussie lead goes over 100.
Fullish and around off, a front foot defense towards cover.
Length ball around off, pushed towards the off side.
Another solid defense from Will as Bumrah lands it around off on a length.
Beaten! This one keeps really low. A length ball just outside off, Warner looks to play but it keeps low and goes below the bat to the keeper.
Full and outside off, driven towards the cover fielder.
Good length and around off, poked towards the cover fielder.
In the channel, angling away outside off. Left alone.
Warner is underway. A length ball just outside off, Warner strokes it through the cover region and scampers back for a couple.
Length ball on middle, Warner tucks it wide of the man at mid on for one.
Length ball around off, worked on the leg side.
Length ball on middle, Warner clips it through square leg for a brace.
Edgy! A length ball just outside off, Warner looks to defend but it goes to second slip off the outside edge. He played with soft hands there, did Warner.
Shortish and around middle, worked to the left of mid on. Ashwin is sharp there.
On middle, worked towards square leg for nothing by Warner.
A sharp bouncer on the last ball. It is around off. Warner does well to get down and sway away.
Fuller length around off, Will defends it back to Siraj.
Shortish on middle, Will looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball just lobs on the on side.
Good running. A shortish length around middle, Pucovski plays it wide of the fielder at mid on and comes back for a brace. Ashwin there was slow in fielding that ball and ends up giving two.
Fuller length around off, Pucovski blocks this out on the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT! This is a beautiful delivery by Siraj. A length ball around off, shapes away affter pitching. Pucovski looks to defend but is surprised by the movement. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards Saha, the substitute keeper, who pouches it nicely by diving to his right. Siraj is rewarded for bowling some good lines here. Australia lose their 1st wicket.
Labuschagne is underway! A fuller ball on the pads, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace. End of a successful over from Siraj.
FOUR! Fine shot from Warner. A fuller ball around middle, Warner strokes it through mid on. No chance for the fielder in the ring. That raced away.
Fuller and outside off, poked towards point.
Short and wide, Warner cuts but finds the point fielder.
Landed around off, blocked by Warner.
Fullish and around off, Warner is solid in defense again.
Two to end the over! Full and outside off, Warner drives it through covers for easy two.
Fuller and around off, Labuschagne pushes it back to the bowler. He looks to throw the ball at the stumps and the striker's end but the throw is wayward as it goes to the keeper. A stare from Siraj.
FOUR! Banged short and Labuschagne nails the pull. It is on middle, he swivels and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Fuller length around off, Marnus is solid in his defense.
A fuller length outside off, driven nicely but straight to covers.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne flicks this on but finds backward square leg.
On a length around off, Labuschagne covers the line and defends this one towards Siraj.
Length on middle, Warner tucks this one towards mid-wicket and takes a quick run.
Length in the channel outside off, Labuschagne leaves that alone.
FOUR! Nice shot. A short and wide ball outside off, Labuscagne cuts this one hard through cover-point for a boundary. You can't bowl short and wide to a player like Labuschagne.
On a length around off, angling in, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Length outside off, Labuschagne punches this one towards deep point for a run.
Fullish outside off, Warner this time drives this nicely straight to the fielder at deep point and exchanges ends.
Floated fuller and around off, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Ashwin has his man early in his spell. Both the Aussie openers dismissed inside the first 10 overs. A tossed up ball around off and middle, Warner gets down and looks to play the sweep but misses to get hit on the pads. Looks pretty good as the Indians appeal. The umpire takes his time and then raises the finger. Warner signals the 'T' after having a word with his partner at the other end. Hot Spot and Snicko detetcs nothing. Ball Tracker shows that the ball would clip the stumps. So, Warner has to go.
Smith is up and running first ball. A flatter ball around off and middle, it is clipped through square leg for a run.
Short and on middle, flicked towards square leg for one.
Another single as Smith pushes this fuller one towards mid on.
Edgy! Tossed up and around off and middle, Marnus comes out of his crease and looks to push it towards mid on but it goes off the inner half. towards mid on.
Back of a length around off, Marnus defends that one.
Length ball around off, tucked straight to square leg.
Length ball around off, defended on the on side by Marnus.
Fullish around middle, Labuscagne flicks but can't beat the fielder at square leg.
Play and a miss! A length ball outside off, Labuschagne loos to drive but connect thin air as the ball misses his outside edge and goes throught to Saha.
Length on middle, played to mid-wicket for nothing.

NOT OUT! A decent review from Ashwin then. That looked like it will miss the leg stump by some margin but that wasn't the case. Loopy ball around the pads, Ashwin swings across the line and misses to get hit on the pad. Indians appeal but it is turned down. Ashwin thinks he has his man as he convinces his not so convinced skipper. Replays later roll on and they show that it would've clipped the leg pole. So, had it been given out, Smith would've been on his bike. For now, the onfield call will stay and India will keep their review.
Floated around off, defended towards silly mid on.
Around off, hit straight to silly mid on again.
Floated around off, Smith plays that with soft hand sand gets an outside edge wide of first slip. They take a single.
Floated around middle, Marnus flicks this one to Rohit at silly mid on.
Around off, blocked by Labuschagne.
Length around off, bounces sharply as Smith plays it down towards gully. His one hand came off the bat as he played the shot.
Fulish around middle, Smith defends this off the front foot.
Around off, Smith blocks this one towards the bowler.
Slightly short around off, Smith looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad. The ball lobs towards gully.
Around off, Smith flicks it to square leg. No ball called as Saini has overstepped here.
Fullish around off, Smith is solid in his defense.
Good over this by Saini. A length on middle, Smith flicks it towards mid-wicket for nothing.
FOUR! Full toss down the pads and Labuschagne is not going to miss out. He slams it through square leg for a boundary. A gift from Ashwin.
tossed up and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Turning in froma around off, nuddhed around the corner for one.
Another one that lands in around off, it turns in as Smith flicks it wide of leg gully. Single taken.
Full and around off, kept out.
Poor ball to end the over. Short and wide, Labuschagne goes back and punches it through covers. They take three. 9 off the over and 50 is up for the Aussies. The lead now reads 144.
Good length and around off, kept out.

Edgy! Good stop at gully from skipper though. Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne looks to punch but it goes off the outer half. It goes to the left of Rahane at gully who dives to catch but it falls short.

Edgy again! Good from Saini so far in this over too. A fuller ball just outside off, Labuschagne looks to drive but the ball takes the outside edge. It goes wide of Rahane this time and they take one.
Full and on middle, flicked wide of mid on by Smith. A single taken.
FOUR! Put away! Short ball on middle, Labuschagne rocks back and pulls it hard through square leg for a boundary.
Short and wide again, punched to deep point for one.
Fuller and on middle, pushed wide of mid on for one.
Tossed up and around middle, pushed through mid on for one.

A muted appeal but turned down. No review from the Indians this time. Tossed up and just outside off, spins in and beats the front foot defense of Labuschagne. He is hit on the back pad. Looks like there is an inside edge. Not sure. Ashwin and Rahane have a chat but this time they are not going for the DRS.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
Labuschagne comes down the track. Ashwin drags the length back. Labuschagne does well to work it on the leg side for a run.
Looped up on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller length around off, Marnus defends this one towards mid-wicket.
Length ball around off, again pushed towards mid-wicket.
Bowls a length outside off, Labushagne punches it straight to covers.
FOUR! Nicely done! On middle and leg, Labuschagne flicks this one through the deep square leg area for his 5th boundary of the innings.
Fuller around off, driven straight towards point.
Length on middle, Marnus tucks but finds square leg.
Floated around off, Smith pushes this on towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Floated around off, Marnus sweeps but finds backward square leg.
Around off, blocked by Marnus.
Flatter around middle, tucked towards deep mid-wicket for another run.

FOUR! More intent from Smith. He is not letting Ashwin settle here. Ashwin tosses it up and Smith accepts the invite. Doesn't quite get to the pitch but goes through with the shot. It goes high in the air but beyond the reach of the fieler inside the ring. A boundary.
On middle, pushed to the right of the bowler. Ashwin looks to field but Labuschagne is in the way. Ashwin cannot get down and stop. A single taken.
Full ball around middle, Smith plays it towards mid-wicket.
Similar ball around middle, Smith is solid in his front foot defense.
Length around middle, Smith tucks it away on the leg side for nothing.
Full and around off, driven to mid off.
Full and on the pads, flicked wide of the man at fine leg for a brace.
Good length and around middle, tucked towards mid on.
Floated outside off, pushed towards the cover region for one.
Lands on middle and turns in, pushed towards mid off of the back foot.
On off, kept out by Smith.
Tossed up and on middle, flicked well but straight to mid-wicket.
Short and wide outside off, Smith punches it through the covers. Rohit gives it a chase and keeps it down to three. They check with the third umpire. It is a clean stop.
Slower through the air and around middle, worked towards square leg for nothing.
Length and around off, keeps a little low. Smith does well to defend.
Around middle on a length, kept out.
Landed on a length and on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Another length ball around off, Smith defends.
FOUR! Drilled through the covers. Lovely shot. Full and outside off, Smith hits it hard through the covers for a boundary. Slightly wide from Bumrah and Smith pounced on it.
Around off, kept out.
Fullish around off, driven nicely bt straight to covers. The fielder there dives to his left and stops a certain boundary.
Length on middle, clipped towards deep square leg for a run.
Fullish on off, Smith drives it straight down the ground. Ashwin from mid on runs to his left and stops the ball.
Length around middle, clipped towards fine leg for another single.
On middle, Marnus defends that one solidly.
On a length around middle, Marnus drives it straight and Ashwin again does well to stop the ball.
Full and around off, Smith covers the line and defends it towards mid on.
Lovely ball from Bumrah. A length ball outside off, straightens after pitching. Smith looks to defend but gets beaten as the ball goes through. Smith acknowledges the ball here.
Fuller length around middle, Smith punches it straight to mid on.
Again on the stumps, kept low but Smith is watchful and blocks this out.
Fuller on middle, clipped to mid-wicket. The ball kept low on this occasion too.
Again a fuller length on middle, Smith blocks this out.
Beaten! a length ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to poke but the ball gets past his outside edge through to Saha.
Fuller ball around off, Marnus drives it straight where Siraj does well to dive to his left and stop the ball.
Full and around off, poked towards point.
Fuller on middle, Marnus flicks this one through the gap at mid-wicket and comes back for three. Ashwin runs and chases the ball but still gives three more. 50 partnership up between these two.
Length around off, shoots up after pitching. Smith is hurried there but defends this one on the off side.
Fuller and around off, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Length around off, defended towards covers.
Fuller on middle, flicked by Labuschagne towards deep square for a run.
Fuller around off, Smith plays it down towards mid off.
Around off pole, Smith covers the line plays it back to the bowler.
Similar ball on off, played towards mid off.
FOUR! SHOT! Fuller and around off, Smith lean on and creams this one through the covers for a boundary. To make things worse, it's a No ball as Saini has overstepped.
Good length and around off, pushed towards point.
Fuller on middle, flicked towards deep square for a run.
Fuller around off, pushed straight to covers. No ball called as Siraj oversteps here.
Length around off, pushed towards point for nothing.
On a length on middle, flicked straight to backward square leg.
On off, Smith just defends this one on the off side.
Fuller again on the off stump, Smith drives it towards covers
A length on middle, flicked towards deep square leg for a brace. The fielder at square leg dived to stop that one but failed to do so and they take a couple.
Angled in from around off, Marnus looks to pull but he is early in the shot. It keeps low as well and hits him on the body.
Good length and just outside off, punched towards cover.
Full and around off, Marnus digs it out towards the right of Gill at covers. He fumbles and gives away a single.
Shortish and on middle, kept out.
Fuller and around middle, pushed to mid on.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Length on middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Length around off, Marnus defends this one out.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the bowler.
Length on middle, Marnus plays it towards silly mid on.
Around middle, pushed towards square leg for nothing.
A solid defense from Labuschagne to a length on middle to finish the over.
Bowls a fullish ball down the leg, Smith misses his flick and the ball goes through to Saha.
On middle, Smith defends this one towards mid-wicket.
Shortish outside off, Smith punches it through to deep point and takes a run.
Around off, Marnus blocks this out.
FOUR! SHOT! Fuller ball on middle, Labuschagne flicks this one through the mid-wicket area and finds a boundary. 100 up for Australia with that shot.
Fuller ball on middle, pushes wide of mid-wicket and takes a run. With that it's STUMPS ON DAY 3.
Bumrah starts with a length ball on off, Labuschagne clips it to mid on first up.

DROPPED! A chance goes abegging! India needed that desparetely and the fielder there drops a sitter there. Length and on middle, Labuschagne clips it uppishly towards square leg where Vihari goes for the catch but spills it in the end. A single taken.
Length and around off, Smith blocks it out off the back foot.
Another length ball on off, Smith blocks it to short mid-wicket this time.
Another good length ball on off, Smith pushes it to the off side.
A single to end the over! Good length on the pads, Smith clips it through square leg and gets a single.
Length and on off, Smith is solid as he blocks it to the off side.
Good length and down leg, Smith makes a leave this time.
Full on middle, Smith pushes it off the back foot towards mid-wicket.
Length and on the pads, Smith helps it on its way to fine leg for a single. AUSTRALIA LEAD BY 200 RUNS!
Good length and around middle, Labuschagne clips it towards square leg where the fielder puts in a dive to field it.
Back of good length on off, solidly defended off the back foot towards mid on.
Length and on off, Smith pushes it to the off side.
Length and on off, Smith turns it to the leg side off the back foot this time.
Another length delivery on the pads, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short of good length on off, Smith plays it to mid on off the back foot.
Slightly fuller and on off, Smith pushes it to short cover this time.
Length and on the pads, Smith flicks it to the man at square leg.
Another good length ball on the pads, Marnus clips it to the man at square leg this time but all along the carpet.
Length and on middle, pushed to mid on by Labuschagne.

A big appeal there but nothing from the umpire. Length and on middle and leg, Labuschagne looks to clip it to the leg side but is beaten. The ball raps him on the pads and there is an appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire. Maybe going down leg as well height might be an issue there.
Length and on off, blocked off the back foot this time. The ball kept a bit low there.
Length and on off, punched off the back foot towards covers.
Length on the pads, clipped towards the leg side for a single.
Length and around the stump line, Labuschagne pushes it to mid on.
BEATEN! Beautiful line for Bumrah! Nervy moment for Labuschagne on 49. Length and just outside off, Marnus looks to have a poke at it but is beaten on the outside edge.

There comes the 50 for Marnus Labuschagne! His 10th in the format! Full and on off, Marnus drives it through mid on where the fielder fumbles to allow the batsmen to cross ends and help Labuschagne get  to his milestone.
Length and on the pads, clipped to the leg side by Smith.
Good length and on the pads, Smith clips it to square leg where Vihari fields it.
On off, Smith blocks it out solidly to the off side.
Fullish around off, Marnus pushes this one towards covers and sets off for a run, but returns after Smith says a loud 'NO'.
Beaten! Lovely ball from Siraj. A length ball outside off, shapes away after pitching. Labuschagne goes for the poke but gets beaten on that as the ball goes through to Saha.
Length around off, Labuschagne pushes this one on the off side.
Around middle, tucked away behind square on the leg side for a run
Fuller around off, Smith fends it back to the bowler.
Similar ball around off, Smith covers the line and blocks this towards the bowler.
Fuller around middle, Labuschagne flicks this one towards mid-wicket.
Fuller this time around off, Marnus plays it towards the fielder at covers.
Around off, Labuschagne defends this one on the off side.
Length ball on middle, Marnus blocks this one towards Bumrah.
Length ball around middle, played towards mid on.
Good over by Bumrah this. A length ball around off, Marnus is solid in his front foot defense.
Back of a length around middle, flicked to the square leg.
Length around off, Smith blocks this one towards mid-wicket.
Good running. A shortish ball outside off, Smith pushes it softly towards covers and goes for a quick run. The fielder has a shy at non striker's end but misses and Smith is well in.

FOUR! LOVELY SHOT! It just gets easy to hit down the ground! Fuller and around off, Labuschagne stays still as he drives it through mid off. The bowler there tries to stop by going to his left but fails to do so as the ball goes onto meet the fence at long off. Excellent timing on that one.
Back of a length around off, Labuschagne defends this on the on side.
Short ball to finish the over. Shortish outside off, Labuschagne initially looks to play but later sways away from it. Good change up this by Siraj.
Tossed up on the pads, clipped towards square leg for a single.
Another floated one on middle Labuschagne pushes it to mid on.
Now he pushes this tossed up ball on middle, Marnus clips it to mid-wicket.
An appeal for LBW turned down! Tossed up around off, Labuschagne goes for the paddle sweep but misses it to get rapped on the pads, An appeal follows from Ashwin but nothing from the umpire.
Floated on leg, clipped to the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Labuschagne looks to defend it out but the ball goes off his outside edge and towards third man for a couple of runs.
Fuller around off, driven straight to mid on.
Length ball around off, Smith pushes this one towards covers.
Fuller on middle, Smith flicks this one to deep mid-wicket and exchanges ends.
Back of a length around off, tucked away towards square leg.
Length around middle, Labuschagne shuffles and tucks this towards fine leg for a run.
Shortish but down the leg side, Smith sways away and lets it go through.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Smith clips it to short mid-wicket. Was in the air for sometime there.
Flatter around middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a single by Labuschagne.
Fuller and on off, driven to short mid on.
Tosed up on the pads, Smith turns it to the leg side for a single.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Tossed up and around off, Labuschagne uses his feet as he gets to the pitch of the ball and then lofts it uppishly towards long off for a boundary.
Floated on off, Marnus is solid on the front foot as he blocks it out with a straight bat.
Back of a length around off, Smith hops and fends it towards covers.
Fuller this time on middle and leg, Smith shuffles and flicks it to square leg. Vihari there dives to his left and stops the ball.
Length on middle, played down to mid on.
Short now on middle and leg, Smith sways away and ducks under it.
Short on middle, Smith goes for the pull, but keeps it down towards fine leg and takes a run.
Length ball on off, Labuschagne defends it back to Siraj. Lead is now 220.
Tossed up ball on off, Smith uses his feet and plays it to short mid on.
Flatter on off, Smith punches it to the off side this time.
Tossed up on the pads, Smith clips it to mid-wicket. Smith has started to use his feet there.
Floated on middle, Smith turns it to the leg side.
Fuller on off, Smith keeps it out right under his eyes there.
Flatter and turning into middle and leg, Smith helps it to the leg side for nothing.
Length and on off, Labuschagne pushes it off the outer half of the bat towards gully for a single.
Back of a length on off, Smith stands tall and bunts it out.
Another back of a length ball on off, Smith is solid on the back foot as he dead bats it onto the pitch.
A play and a miss! Length and outside off, Smith tries to force it through the off side without any footwork but is beaten on the inside edge there.
Length and on the pads, Smith flicks it to the leg side this time.
Length and on the pads, Smith clips it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Marnus plays it from within the crease.
Flatter on off, pushed to covers.
Floated on middle, Labuschagne sweeps it through square leg for a single.
On the pads, Smith clips it to short fine leg.
On off, kept out.
Floated on off, pushed to short leg this time.
Length around of, pushed on the leg side by Marnus.
Three taken. A shortish ball outside off, Labuschagne drives this on the up through the cover point area. Agarwal the substitute chases the ball and pulls it back in time.
Length around off, Smith plays it towards cover.
On a length around off, Smith guides this one to point for nothing.
Fuller this time around off, Smith blocks this one towards covers solidly.
Fuller length just outside off, Smith prods forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on the pads, Labuschagne clips it to short fine leg.
On off, pushed to the bowler.
FOUR! Innovative shot! 100-run stand is up between the two, Ashwin floats one on off, Labuschagne brings out the reverse sweep and gets a boundary at third man.
On off, pushed through the off side for a single this time.
Floated on the pads, clpped through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Floated on off, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Taken down the leg side! The substitute keeper Saha takes a sensational take! A crucial stand is broken. Bowls a fast one on a length on leg, Labuschagne as he does so well looks to help it on its way to the leg side but the extra bit of bounce there means the ball goes off the edge and towards the left of the keeper. Saha, the substitute keeper dives full length to that side to pouch it. Can India capitalise on this opening?
Full on middle, Wade clips it to square leg.
Full on off, Wade drives it off the front foot towards mid off.
FOUR! Elegantly done! Full and straight outside off, Wade comes on the front foot and then drives it through mid off for a boundary. He gets off the mark there.
Length and outside off, Wade makes a leave there.
Length and angled into the pads, Wade somehow manages to fend it to the leg side. A successful over for India and Saini.
Tossed up on off, Smith plays it with soft hands towards point for a quick single.
Tossed up on off, Wade punches it off the back foot towards covers.
Another tossed up ball on off, Wade pushes it to covers.
Outside off, left alone.
Another ball outside off, Wade does not offer a shot to it.
Floated on off, Wade brings out the front foot defensive stroke there.
Length and on off, pushed to covers.
Back of a length on off, tapped to point by Smith.
FOUR! Handsomely done! Length and outside off, Smith watches the ball and then creams the drive through cover-point to fetch a boundary.
Back of a length on off, pushed to the bowler off the back foot.
Fuller and on off, Smith clips it through mid-wicket and gets a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! EDGED AND GONE! Wade's poor run continues as Saini has his second of the innings. Beautifully bowled there by Navdeep Saini. Bowls a length ball and gets it to rear up a bit around off, Wade looks to defend it off the back foot but ends up getting a thick outside edge which is pouched safely by the substitute keeper, Saha.
Length and on off, pushed to the on side by Smith.
Good length and on off, Smith defends it out off the front foot this time.

FOUR! Crunched! No matter what happens on the other end Smith will continue what he does the best, score runs. Full and on off, Smith leans in to the drive and creams it through covers for a boundary.
On a length and on off, Smith pushes it to mid on.
On a length and on off, Smith plays it to mid on once again.
On a length and on off, blocked off the crease to the off side by Smith.
Length and on middle, Green looks to clip it to the leg side but the ball goes of the leading edge towards covers. Lucky for him it goes along the ground.
Good length and on off, kept out to the off side by Green.
Length and outside off, left alone by Cameron Green.
Off the mark is Green! Length and angled into middle, Green clips it through square leg for a single.
On a length and on off, Smith plays it to mid-wicket.
A short of good length on off, a sharp rise there a Smith is surprised there. In the end, he does well to fend it onto the pitch there.
In the channel outside off, left alone by Green.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery by Bumrah. A length ball around off, straightens after pitching and goes through to the keeper beating the outside edge of Green.
Fuller around middle, blocked solidly by Green.
Length around off, Green prods forward and plays it towars mid on.

FOUR! EDGY! A fuller length around off, Green looks to play it on the leg side, but gets an outside which goes to the left of Pujara at wide first slip towards the third man fence. The pitch has started doing its trick here. AUSTRALIA LEAD BY 251 RUNS!
Length ball around off, pushed towards point for nothing.
FIFTY FOR STEVEN SMITH. A short ball around off, Smith pulls this one through square leg and collect a run. 2nd fiffty for Smith in the match and he would like to continue.
Length and on the pads, Smith clips it to fine leg for a single. He moves to 49 with that.
Length and on off, played to point where the fielder cuts it off.
Length and on off, Green defends it off the inner half of the bat towards square leg.
Short of good length and on off, Green stands tall and fends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Beautifully driven! Full and around off, Green comes on the front foot and then drives it through mid off as the ball beats the fielder there to go to the long off boundary.

FIFTY For Steve Smith. His second of the match. He is back in his original form and how. A shortish ball around off, pulled through towards deep square leg for a run. He would like to continue the same way and convert it into another ton. The longer he bats the more Australia extend the lead.
Fuller length around off, blocked on the off side by Green.

Overthrows! Length and on off, Green pushes it to mid off and takes off for a run, Smith sends him back as the fielder has a shy at the keeper's end. He misses it and the ball goes to fine leg. The batsmen take a single in the end.
Short on middle, Smith pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On off, Smith keeps it out.
On a length on off, Smith defends it to the side of the pitch on the leg side.
Length around off, Smith fends this out.
Back of a length on middle, Smith pushes it back to Saini.
Length ball around off, Smith plays it back to the bowler.
Length around off, Smith defends this one towards mid off.
A length ball coming in around off, Smith covers the line and blocks it back to the bowler.
Length ball around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for nothing.
Floated on off, Green keep it out right under his eyes.
On off, kept out to the bowler.
Fuller on off, pushed to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Green does well to push it down to the bowler.
Coming from round the wicket to Green. Tossed this one up on off, Green is solid in defense.
Floated on middle and leg, clipped towards the leg side for a single by Green.
Length and on off, Green plays it to straightish mid on this time.
On a length on off, Green pushes it back to the bowler.
Short of good length but not short enough to pull. Green still goes with it and takes the blow onto his body.
Fuller and on off, Green defends it out to the leg side.
On a good length on off, Green gets on top of the bounce and pushes it to the off side.
Green is standing way outside his crease to negotiate the extra zip there. Length and on off, Green plays it to mid on to see off the over from Siraj.
Tossed up on off, clipped to short fine leg.
Tossed up on middle and leg, clipped past short leg and towards mid-wicket.
Another loopy ball on middle, Smith flicks it to mid on.
On off, Smith keeps his bat and pad together as he defends it out.
Flatter and on off, Smith rocks back and manages to punch it back to the bowler.
Flighted on the pads, Smith clips it towards fine leg and gets a brace this time. AUSTRALIA LEAD BY 262 RUNS!
Back of a length around off, defended towards mid-wicket.
On a length around off, played back to the bowler by Green.
Fuller around off, Green prods forward and drives it towards mid off.
Length on middle, Green pushes this past silly mid on and takes off for a run but returns as his partner says 'NO'.
Length around middle, Green clips this through deep square leg and comes back for a brace.
Length ball outside off, Green pushes and hits it straight to gully.
Carrom ball outside leg, clipped on the leg side for a run.
Fuller this time around off, driven straight back to Ashwin.
Floated around middle, Grren comes down the track and defends this one back to Ashwin.
Fuller and outside off, Green drives it to covers for a single.

GREEN IS SAFELY IN! Floated on middle, Smith whips it towards mid-wicket and gets a brace as the fielder throws the ball to the bowler there. Ashwin whips the bails off and asks the question as the umpire takes it upstairs. Replays come in and Green is safe there as he makes his ground.
On leg, Smith helps it to short fine leg for a dot.
Length around off, blocked solidly on the off side by Green.
Fullish ball outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Good length around middle and off, Green blocks this out on the off side.
Back of a length around off, Green stands tall and hits it back to the bowler.
On middle, Green tucks this one towards short mid-wicket.
Length around off, played down to mid on for nothing. Good over this by Siraj.
Fuller on off, Smith pushes it to mid on.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Smith tucks it to fine leg and scampers for a single.
On off, blocked by Green.
Another tossed up ball on off, Green is happy to keep it out.
Floated on leg, Green helps it on its way to the fine leg region for a single.
Fuller on middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler there by Smith.
Bowls a fullish ball on middle, Green drives it straight to mid on.
Length around middle, flicked towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
FOUR! Nicely driven. A fullish ball around off, Green lunges forward and drives this past mid off for a boundary. Excellent shot this by Green
Fuller length around off, Green prods forward and defends this one towards mid off.

That was close. A fuller length ball around middle and leg, Green looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Loud appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire. Rahane is not interested in taking the review and rightly so as replays show there was some bat there. A good ball this from Siraj.
Length ball around off, Green drives this one towards covers and thinks for a run but returns back. Vihari there has a shy at the striker's end but hits Green there and immediately apologizes.
Flatter and going down leg, Smith looks to pull it but misses it. Good take there by Saha.
Flatter outside off, Smith slaps it through covers for a single.
On off, kept out off the back foot by Green.
Floated on middle and leg, clipped to short fine leg.
Tossed up outside off, Green blocks it from within the crease.
Full on leg, Green clips it through mid-wicket and gets a single. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4! AUSTRALIA LEAD BY 276 RUNS!
Length and on off, pushed to mid on by Green there.
Good length and around off, Green pushes to the off side for a single.

SIX! That's gone the distance! Short and on middle, Smith pulls it fine over fine leg and gets a top edge on it. The ball sails over the fence for a biggie. Looks to be the norm of the session though.
FOUR! Helped on its way! Full and angled into the pads, Smith flicks it through square leg and gets a boundary now.
Another fuller one off, clipped towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full on off, kept out off the front foot by Green.
Full on leg, pushed to mid on.
FOUR! On the charge here! Tossed up on middle, Swith sweeps it towards deep square leg and gets a boundary. 50-run stand comes up between these two.
Floated on leg, clipped to fine leg for a single.
Floated on middle. pushed to the bowler.
Another tossed up ball this time on off, Green pushes it to the off side now.
Tossed up on leg, tucked towards short leg there.
Length around off, defended solidly towards covers by Smith.
Length on the pads, clipped thorugh deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length around middle, Green tucks this one towards deep square for another run.
FOUR! Helped on its way. A fuller ball on the pads, Smith tucks this one fine towards the fine leg boundary. He is now looking to score runs at a good pace.
Length on middle, flicked towards square leg for a run. The fileder dives and stops the ball but could not prevent the single. Australia now lead by 300 runs.
Fulller length on middle, Green defends this on towards mid on.
Tossed up on off, Smith comes to the pitch of the ball and then pushes it to covers for a single.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler by Green.
Flatter on off, punched off the back foot towards covers for a single.

OUT! LBW! THREE REDS! Just what India wanted and the technology comes to their assistance there. Ashwin bowls a nice tossed up ball around off,  gets it to turn a bit towards Smith. Steven there comes on the front foot to defend but the ball spins past him and raps him flush on the pads. Ashwin appeals and there is a shake of head from the umpire. Rahane signals 'T' immediately. Replays roll in. Firstly it is a fair delivery as Hot Spot does not show bat involved. Snicko comes in and confirms the same. Time for Hawk Eye now. Pitching in line, Impact in Line and Wickets Hitting. Three reds and Smith has to take the long walk back. India would be relieved to see the back of Steven Smith and now would hope to wrap the Australian innings quickly to set up the chase here.
On off, Paine keeps it out off the front foot.
Another floated ball on off, Paine watchfully keeps it out once again. A successful over for Ashwin and India there.
Length ball around middle, Green looks to turn that one on the leg side but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Fuller around middle, clipped straight to short mid-wicket.
Back of a length around middle, turned towards mid-wicket for nothing.
Shortish around off, Green stands tall and blocks this out.
